title: po lo chi(pineapple chicken)
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in a mixture of water, soy and cornstarch and salt.
Saute onions and remove from pan.
Saute celery and water chestnuts; remove from pan.
Saute chicken until brown.
Add vegetables (crisp) and pineapple and finally the juice and simmer gently until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot with rice.

title: almond wreaths
directions: Cream the butter until softened.
Gradually add the sugar, creaming until fluffy after each addition.
Blend the well beaten egg in thirds.
Add the flour in fourths, blending well after each addition.
Chill dough in refrigerator several hours.
Remove one-half the dough from refrigerator and turn onto a lightly floured surface.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut rounds with a lightly floured 1 3/4-inch round cookie cutter.
Using a lightly floured 3/4-inch round cookie cutter, cut out centers of the cookies. Brush cookies lightly with a slightly beaten egg yolk.
Sprinkle cookies with the chopped almonds.
Carefully transfer to the cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
With a spatula, carefully remove cookies to cooling rack.
Repeat above procedure for remainder of dough.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and stir.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch casserole in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cream together mayonnaise and cream cheese; add to jello.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Pour into favorite mold and chill until set.
Turn out on lettuce and garnish with fresh blueberries.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello in boiler and let come to boil just enough to melt it all.
Then mix in cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Easy and delicious.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
In saucepan, combine oleo, cocoa, shortening and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over the dry ingredients and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix buttermilk, soda and vanilla; add to the mixture.
Mix well. Grease and flour a 1 x 11 x 15-inch pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, syrup, and sugar and microwave 4 minutes. Remove.
Add 6 cups of corn flakes (I use more).
Stir until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients in a microwavable bowl for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir, heat 2 more minutes.
Add soda and stir.

title: conga bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook vanilla pudding as directed.
Let cool.
Set overnight. Spread vanilla pudding on bottom, not too thick (1/2 inch), slice bananas around on pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Start all over with second layer.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Bake in 2 bread box pans that have been greased at 300° about 1 hour.

title: puppy chow
directions: Microwave:
Combine chips and vegetable oil.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until chocolate melts.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over Crispix.
Place powdered sugar in a big Tupperware bowl.
Add coated cereal.
Seal.
Shake until cereal is thoroughly coated. Refrigerate.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Beat oleo, Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add flour, salt, vanilla, baking powder and milk.

title: chicken casserole ii
directions: Pour melted butter over stuffing mix and stir.
Place 2/3 stuffing in bottom of casserole dish, cover with chicken and top with sour cream and soup mixture.
(Combine soup, sour cream and 1/4 cup broth before spreading over chicken.)
Continue layers; top with remaining stuffing.
Pour remaining broth over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples and cider slowly 12 to 14 hour or overnight.
Drain off some of the juice if apples are juicy.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves and cook 1 hour or until it gets as thick as you like it. Makes 8 cups.
Can freeze or keep in refrigerator.

title: colonial pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, spices and salt.
Beat together until well creamed.
Beat in pumpkin slowly at low mixer speed. Gradually add milk. Stir until well combined.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 50 minutes longer.

title: meatballs
directions: Put a little oil in pan and fry two garlic cloves and pepperoni until garlic is soft. Add two Tbsp of sweet basil. Add can of whole or peeled tomatoes and small glass of water;
simmer until tomatoes are boiled down. Cook ditaline and mix with a can of pork and beans. Heat thoroughly.

title: taco party wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place wings in plastic bag.
Add remaining ingredients and shake to mix.
Place in a single layer on a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Turn and bake 10 minutes longer or until tender.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on flour tortillas. Roll and refrigerate overnight. Cut into small slices with sharp knife and enjoy!

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Boil long grain rice 20 minutes.
Drain.
Put into large bowl. Simmer shrimp and spaghetti sauce over medium to low heat 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and pour over rice.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, nutmeg, onion and egg. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Brown quickly and place in large casserole.
Make gravy using 2 tablespoons each of flour and meat drippings (you may need to add some other fat) for every cup of gravy desired.
Brown flour in fat, add cold water and stir until gravy is smooth and thickens.
Cover and bake at 325° about 1 hour. I usually use 3 cups of water for 1 pound of meat.
You can also refrigerate this for 2 or 3 days and then bake.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture, alternately with whipped cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: quick bavarian cream
directions: Substitute other flavors for gelatin and juice, if you wish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (batter will be soupy).

title: white salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar until latter is dissolved, then add the gelatin.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: white spaghetti
directions: Boil the spaghetti in water and 1 teaspoon olive oil.
The olive oil will prevent the spaghetti from sticking together. Drain spaghetti and return it to the pot.
Do not put it over heat again!
Mix butter with spaghetti first, then mix milk, parsley and garlic powder.
Last, mix in Parmesan cheese.
Serve with salad and it makes a quick, easy meal that children and adults love.

title: lattice-topped turkey pie
directions: Combine
first 10 ingredients in large bowl; stir well. Spoon into a lightly greased long baking dish.

title: fish with zucchini and red pepper
directions: Place fish into baking dish.
Top with vegetables; arrange red pepper over top.
Cook on Medium for 10 to 15 minutes, covered with wax paper, rearranging once (fish) during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: rose petal beads("a family heirloom")
directions: Start early in rose season and make all summer long.

title: crispix minglers
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine cereal, crackers and pretzels. Drizzle the oil over all and mix well. Microwave 4 minutes. Pour into a large brown paper bag and sprinkle dry dressing mix over mixture. Shake well. Add nuts (optional).

title: cheesecake(easy, super delicious, lower calorie)
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar and add the rest of the ingredients, beating in eggs one at a time.
Blend until smooth. Press regular graham cracker crust into bottom of 9 to 10-inch spring-form pan, slightly thicker at bottom pan seam and then up to middle of pan sides.
Gently pour mixture into pan.

title: fresh strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add water, then egg yolks, well beaten. Beat well and add to hot milk.
Cook until thick as mayonnaise. Cool; add vanilla, cream and berries.
Freeze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southwestern casserole
directions: Mix
together and keep bubbly on stove (careful, it can stick to	pan).
Layer
an
11 x 13-inch pan with nacho cheese flavored Doritos generously and then crunch down.
When ready to
serve, add meat over Doritos.
Next shredded lettuce, then diced tomatoes,
then
3	cups shredded Monterey Jack cheese, then sliced
black olives.
Heat in broiler just until cheese melts. Serve
immediately.
Top
with
sour
cream.
Leftover Doritos, serve on the side.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute
onion
in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually
add
milk;
cook,
stirring constantly until thickened. Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese, stir until cheese melts. Toss potatoes in
cheese
sauce, reserving 1 cup of potatoes. Pour into 2 quart casserole.
Arrange ham and remaining potato slices on
top
of casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: sherbet with fresh fruit
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, peel and slice kiwi fruit and slice banana into 4 dessert bowls.
Arrange sliced kiwi fruit and banana.
Top each with a scoop of sherbet.
Garnish with chocolate curls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spanish rice with tuna
directions: In a heavy deep pot, saute onion, celery and parsley in a small amount of oil.
When soft, add tuna, uncooked rice and 8 ounces of water.
Cook for 30 minutes, adding the boiling water as necessary.
When cooked, spread in a shallow dish and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: caldereta
directions: Marinate beef in mixture of vinegar, peppercorn, salt and crushed garlic for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Fry pieces of beef in cooking oil.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Pour in tomato sauce and boiling water.
Add the green pepper, bay leaf and hot sauce, as desired.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Blend in liver spread.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 5.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Cut flour into softened lard.
Pour vinegar into milk and let stand for a few minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and shape in a ball.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Separate into small balls and roll into pie crusts.
Dough may be frozen or kept in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: excellent jewish apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon, apples and 1/4 cup sugar together and set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt or funnel pan well with shortening.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together well.
Add other ingredients; beat well.
Alternate layers of batter and apples, starting and ending with the batter.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Cut chocolate in small pieces.
Add sugar, butter or margarine, salt, syrup and cream.
Cover and boil 5 minutes. Uncover.
Boil slowly, stirring constantly, to firm ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and stir until blended.
Pour quickly over nuts which have been placed in a well buttered pan. When cool, cut in squares.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Add soup with 1/4 cup of water, Kitchen Bouquet, salt, pepper and potatoes (sliced) into crock-pot.
Cook on slow/low for 6 hours.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Stirring constantly, heat sugar, milk and cocoa on high.
Heat until it reaches a fast, rolling boil.
Reduce heat to maintain a slow, rolling boil for at least 5 minutes, still stirring constantly.
After 5 minutes, reduce heat to lowest setting and add peanut butter, vanilla, marshmallow cream and butter.
Mix thoroughly and quickly pour into a shallow pan (about 9 x 1-inch). Allow to cool.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Cook the shrimp in simmering salted water for 3 to 4 minutes. Drain and cool.
Peel and clean.
Arrange in a crock or dish in alternate layers with sliced onions, bay leaves, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Add lemon slices, capers, herbs and enough olive oil just to cover and lemon juice to taste.
Let the shrimp stand for 4 to 5 hours in the refrigerator to mellow.
Delicious with thin rye bread and butter sandwiches, radishes and cucumber salad.

title: curried bean salad bake
directions: Heat butter, onion, green pepper and curry powder (should be put in hot butter first).
Cook until tender.
Add fruit cocktail, kidney beans, tomatoes, brown sugar, vinegar, bay leaf, dried thyme, salt, pepper and dash of red pepper sauce.
Bake at 350° in casserole for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Serve hot or cold (for summer).

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order as listed.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss salad when ready to serve, if desired.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, canned milk and cocoa in saucepan. Bring to a boiling stage of 230° to 240° until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and pecans. Beat with mixer until mixture becomes thick.
Pour into buttered dish and cool completely.

title: cake(kids kitchen)
directions: You get the pizza at the grocery store.
You take it
home and put it in the microwave like thing.
Then warm it up.
Then you can cut it up.
Then it's ready.

title: pickled fish
directions: Heat oil in a large frypan.
Season fish with salt and pepper. Fry fish until lightly browned on both sides.
Remove from oil and place on a paper towel.
Place onion slices in a 2-quart casserole.
Add vinegar, turmeric, curry powder, chili peppers, ginger root and bay leaves.
Cook over a low heat.
Remove from heat when mixture begins to boil.
Place fillets in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Pour vinegar mixture over fillets.
Turn fillets once.
Let mixture cool to room temperature.
Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 days.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: topping for fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine or butter.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Peel and slice peaches.
Add tapioca.
Add to the unbaked pie crust.
Add the topping mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until brown at 350°.

title: crunchy snack mix
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook and stir together brown sugar, butter and syrup over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Let boil without stirring for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add vanilla and pour over cereal mixture. Stir gently to coat.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir after first 15 minutes.
Spread on foil to cool.
Keep in a tightly covered container.
Makes 8 cups.

title: green punch
directions: Make jello with water.
Add rest of ingredients except 7-Up. Refrigerate.
Add 7-Up before serving.
Serves 25 cups.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Add soda to buttermilk in a 4-quart saucepan.
Stir well and let stand one minute.
Add sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Cook to soft-ball stage, 236° to 238°.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until begins to thicken.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: crab salad
directions: This is what we call a "so and so much" recipe.
You use so and so much of each ingredient to suit your taste.
There are no hard and fast measurements.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix pecans
and coconut.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Mix	cake mix according to directions on box. Pour batter over pecans and coconut.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt the brown sugar and oleo together and set aside.
Mix the white sugar and cinnamon together.
Toss the quartered biscuits into the cinnamon and sugar mixture. Roll around until all covered.
Place in Bundt pan that has been greased. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pull apart when serving warm.

title: maui pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill at least 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix cheese at room temperature; add 3 other ingredients. Top with chopped parsley or chopped nuts. (This can be done as a cheese ball, but it's rather soft and works better as a dip.)

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tex-mex
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Drain and return sausage to skillet. Stir in rice, beans and sauce. Cook until thoroughly heated, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Heat salsa and chicken, stirring occasionally.
Make your rice, following directions. Pour salsa chicken and rice.
Makes about 4 servings.
Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole(low-fat)
directions: Dice chicken and mix together with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Fairly low in fat without almonds.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni.
Brown sausage and onion.
Add macaroni after it is cooked.
Mix all this together.
Top with 4 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni slices (1 package).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy party mix
directions: Combine all cereals, pretzels and nuts in a large container. Combine the other ingredients in a saucepan and heat until oleo is melted.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix thoroughly to coat dry ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 200° to 250°, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: tip top tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion in butter; add green pepper.
Continue cooking until tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in flour until blended.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, sugar and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Add tuna and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cut oleo into flour and nuts.
Press onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in oven for 15 minutes at 350° until light brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Dredge tomatoes in cornmeal mixture.
Heat oil in a large skillet to 375°.
Add tomatoes and fry until golden brown on each side. Drain on paper towels.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown onion, garlic and hamburger in large frypan.
In Dutch oven put everything else.
Drain meat mixture and add to Dutch oven.
Heat over medium-low heat for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: mock lobster
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil.
Add salt, pepper, celery salt, vinegar and chopped onion to the water.
Cut fish into bite size pieces.
Add fish to the boiling water and cook gently for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with melted margarine and lemon juice for dipping.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: finnish oven pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, add milk and the dry ingredients.
Melt 1/2 stick of oleo in a 9 inch pie pan.
Add 1 cup of mix into pie pan.
Bake at 425 for 1/2 hour.
This recipe makes 3 or 4 pans.
Eat with syrup or cream cheese, sausage, etc.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix together.
Will be a thin batter. Pour into funnel; let run into a skillet of hot oil.
Makes into circles like lace until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours or cut recipe in half and bake 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
One half of recipe will ser`ve 3 to 4. Don't salt or brown meat.
The gravy will be dark brown.
Delicious.
Do not dilute soup with water.
Add the soup undiluted to the meat.

title: hertzler donuts
directions: Let rise until double and deep fat fry.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a jar.
Mix 1 to 2 tablespoons with a cup of boiling water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Put broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over broccoli.
Mix together the soup and milk; pour over the broccoli.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top; bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: sour cream and cinnamon cake
directions: Mix margarine, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon in bowl until crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Combine cake mix, oil, sugar, sour cream and eggs in mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes or until smooth.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into greased tube pan. Sprinkle with half the pecan mixture.
Top with remaining batter; sprinkle with remaining pecan mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool in pan for 1 hour.
Invert onto serving plate.
May bake for several minutes longer for crispy side.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: christmas fruit cups
directions: Mix well.
Bake in small muffin tins with liners at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger until gray looking; add chili powder, salt, sugar and catsup.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hot bun with cole slaw.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and whirl until smooth. Transfer to medium size bowl with cover.
Chill until ready to use.

title: best roast beef(prime rib)
directions: Rub the roast with salt and pepper.
Place fat side up in a shallow pan and roast in a preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn off the heat, but do not open the oven door.
No matter how long it is until dinner time, don't open door or remove roast.
Turn it on to 375° again 30 to 40 minutes before serving time.
Does not matter about the size of roast.

title: sausage hash brown bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain on paper towels.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to roaring boil, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add either peanut butter or chocolate chips.
Stir well. Add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate until cooled.
Cut and store in airtight container.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Stir in nuts, dates, cherries and chocolate pieces.
In a small bowl beat eggs and sugar.
Stir into flour mixture.
Turn into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top is golden and pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely, top side up on rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine crumbled Top Ramen noodles, sesame seed, almonds, cabbage, onions and green peppers.
Mix well.
Add oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and chicken packet from Top Ramen noodles. Mix well.
Set in refrigerator for 2 or more hours until noodles are soft.
Can stir occasionally.

title: watercress-zucchini soup
directions: Saute leeks in butter in a Dutch oven 3 minutes. Stir in zucchini and saute 2 minutes. Add broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes. Add watercress and pepper.
Simmer 1 minute.
Spoon 1/3 of soup mixture into container of an electric blender and puree.
Repeat process twice until all mixture is pureed.
Stir in whipping cream.
Chill.
Yields 7 1/3 cups.

title: virginia's ice cream
directions: Beat well and put in ice cream freezer, then finish filling to fill mark on can of freezer with milk.
If you add fruit, mix it in last.
It tastes better if made the night before and let set in the deep freezer.
Makes 5 quarts if you don't add the fruit.
Add less sugar, about 1 3/4 cups or to taste, depending on the type of fruit being used.

title: 55 minute yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Measure shortening, sugar and salt into mixing bowl.
Pour scalded milk over these ingredients; stir to mix. Cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
When milk mixture is cooled, add dissolved yeast.
Add flour; stir well after addition of each cupful.
Beat together about 60 strokes; turn into greased bowl.
Cover bowl; allow to rise until double in bulk in warm place.
Make into rolls.
Let rise about 3/4 hour.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: viola's one egg cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and egg.
Add the flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Cook at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
You may use any desired topping.

title: party mushroom spread
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions in oil in skillet over medium high heat until excess liquid has evaporated and mushrooms are just beginning to brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and mustard; heat but do not boil.
Serve as a spread on Melba rounds or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fabulous dip
directions: Combine soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and spinach.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, dip center of bread out in small pieces, saving pieces to use with dip.
Pour dip into center of bread.

title: coconut pie(diet)
directions: Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl until softened.
Beat in gradually the Equal; add whipping cream and water.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut extract and Cool Whip.
Spoon into dish and chill for 4 hours.
Garnish with about 2 tablespoons fresh grated coconut.

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Scald milk, add sugar, butter and salt; stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water (warm 110° to 115°).
Stir in milk mixture, eggs and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add remaining 1 cup flour gradually.
Turn onto lightly floured pastry cloth; knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn dough in bowl to lightly grease top; cover, chill overnight.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart in two greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch cake pans; cover.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour, uncover.
Bake in 375° (gas oven) 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan; serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: venison swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender, not brown.
Combine meat, crumb mix, egg, onion, parsley flakes and seasonings.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons butter, shaking skillet to keep balls round.
Remove meatballs.
Mix flour and water and stir into drippings in skillet.
Add broth and coffee.
Replace meatballs. Heat and serve.

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugars with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add egg and extract and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts (optional).
Mix until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Press each ball around a kiss (like chocolate covered cherry).
Bake 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. (Do not overbake.)
Cool on wire racks.
Frost or decorate as desired.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: mock lasagne casserole
directions: Brown the meat; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, pepper, basil and 1/2 cup water.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake as directed.
Split layers to make 4.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: peanut crunch
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from stove and stir in peanut butter thoroughly.
Mix in corn flakes and stir well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix sugar, spices and salt in a large bowl. Beat water and egg white together.
Add to sugar mixture. Add nuts, coating well. Place on 2 greased cookie sheets. Bake for 45 minutes at 275°. Remove at once.
Store in airtight container.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: lazy (not) stuffed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in large baking dish.
Cook the meat and onion soup in large skillet over medium heat until well browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
(May prepare in advance and refrigerate until ready to bake.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain juice off meat and break into pieces with fork.
Put all ingredients in large bowl and fold in sauce of mayonnaise and vinegar.

title: crab quesadillas
directions: Mix butter and oil.
Use all but 2 tablespoons butter/oil mixture to saute onion and garlic.
Cool, add remaining ingredients, except for cheese and tortillas.

Brush tortillas with remaining butter/oil mixture, warm in skillet, buttered side down. Place crab mixture on half of unbuttered tortilla side, top with cheese, fold in half and bake at 500° for 5 minutes.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Mix in eggs; slowly add flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in milk, vanilla and bananas. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown the meat in a large pot. Stir in onions and celery. Cook 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic powder. Add beans and cover. Lower heat. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: gooey rolls
directions: Take rolls that you have let thaw in the refrigerator and cut each one in half.
Pat down to 1-inch thick.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan, a Bundt pan or an angel food cake pan.
Roll each piece of dough in 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture.
Place each piece in pan.
Now mix melted butter, pudding, vanilla and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spoon over top of rolls.
Let rise 1 hour or longer until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
These rolls can be made the night before, just don't thaw dough.
Work with it the same way, but start with frozen dough. When you get up they will be ready to place in the oven.

title: salmon pate
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Form into ball or log, or place in bowl.
Chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add beaten egg yolks and mashed bananas.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add to the mixture.
Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Makes 1 loaf.

title: apple fudge squares
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over medium heat.
Add sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda, salt and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8-inch square greased pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine jello and water, let thicken in refrigerator and then whip until fluffy and stiff.
Whip cold milk until thick and fluffy; combine.
Add strawberries, lemon juice and sugar to taste.
Pour into large bowl or bowls lined with angel food cake. Let set for several hours before serving.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut; press out liquid.
Cut cheese slices in half.
Sprinkle kraut on chicken.
Top with cheese; pour dressing over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: curried chicken
directions: Simmer raisins in water 5 minutes, until raisins absorb water. Stir in soup, milk, chicken and curry.
Heat.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter crumble bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, shortening, peanut butter and eggs until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder. Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining dough in ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Mix reserved 1 1/2 cups dough and the candies. Crumble into pan, pressing lightly.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fend for yourself stir-fry
directions: Saute broccoli, onion and bell pepper for 5 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
After 5 minutes, add Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce, then simmer for 30 seconds. Serve over rice.

title: peachy glazed ham steaks
directions: Mix reserved peach juice, the brown sugar and mustard in a 10-inch skillet; bring to boil over medium-high heat. Cook 2 minutes or until liquid is slightly reduced. Add ham slices; cook 2 minutes per side or until heated through. Reduce heat; add peaches and green onions. Cover and cook about 3 minutes until peaches are hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate-strawberry cake
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a larger mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate and eggs.
Beat mixture thoroughly.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with milk. Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Add jam and mix well.
Fold in sliced berries.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing and top with fresh, whole strawberries, rolled in confectioners sugar.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Using a fork, beat together vinegar, egg and water.
Gently work this into flour mixture, adding liquid only until mixture will cling together when pressed into a ball.
Divide into two portions.
Roll out 1 portion to 1/8-inch thickness for bottom crust.
Fit into 9-inch pie pan.
(Bake at 450° if not for fruit pie.)
Refrigerate bottom crust along with other half of dough (for lattice top) until filling is cooked and ready to use.

title: baked halibut or salmon
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Butter
bottom of baking dish large enough
for fish.
Crumble saltines in a plastic bag and sprinkle or
spoon over fish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until fish loses its translucent quality (until it flakes with a fork).

title: cherry pepper shooters
directions: Slice off and discard stems from the cherry peppers.
With a small spoon, scoop out and discard seeds.
Cut the Prosciutto into 1 to 2-inch squares.
Cut each pineapple chunk in half and wrap in Prosciutto.
Stuff into a pepper.
Serves 12.
Preparation time: 20 minutes. Cooking time: 0 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: In bowl, mix cornmeal, flour and so on.
Dip hot dogs in mixture.
Deep-fry (slowly) at 375° until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, water, eggs and cracker meal.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until brown and set.
Place in skillet.
Mix together jelly and chili sauce.
Pour over meat.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Brown sausage and ground beef together and drain. Add spaghetti sauce to beef mixture. Add black pepper, garlic salt, and oregano. Layer starting with 1/2 meat mixture. Then add half noodles, half cottage cheese, 2 cups of mozzarella cheese, 1 cup cheddar cheese. Repeat but leave the meat mixture for the top.

title: pork chops or chicken
directions: Mix the soups, water and rice.
Salt and pepper the meat.
Lay the meat on top of mixture.
Put foil over it.
Bake 45 minutes. Remove foil and brown 15 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and cardamon.
Add to creamed mixture with milk.
In a small bowl, mix remaining sugar and cardamon.
Dip rounded spoonfuls of dough in sugar mixture.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with pineapple, oranges and cottage cheese. Then add marshmallows and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in baking dish.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix well. Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in a 6-quart boiler and add water.
Cover and boil for 30 minutes. While chicken is cooking, cut and microwave the carrots, potatoes and celery.
After chicken is done, remove from broth and set aside.
Add soup and stir with wire whisk.
Add bouillon, carrots, potatoes, celery and peas.
Simmer. Cut chicken into small chunks and add to simmering vegetables.
Prepare bottom pie shell according to package directions in a deep dish pie pan. Do not bake. Add filling to bottom pie shell.
Put a pie shell on top to make a top crust.
Make slits in the top with a knife. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until top crust is brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray a 3-quart casserole dish with Pam. Break spaghetti into 2-inch lengths.
Cook in boiling salt water. Drain well.

title: sylvester's chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Bisquick, white sugar, nuts and milk.
Put batter into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
In separate pan, melt chocolate chips in water. Pour over batter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pudding will rise to top and sauce to bottom.
Serve in bowls and dip sauce over pudding.
Best served warm.

title: "banana delite"(camp fire dessert)
directions: You will also need heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer.
Serves 36 sandwiches.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, boil rice and water 10 minutes.
Add 1-quart milk and margarine.
Slowly boil, covered, for 30 minutes. Stir often.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Take off heat and add beaten eggs and raisins.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add vanilla. Pour into a 2-quart dish and sprinkle with topping.
Chill.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is boiled out.
Add applesauce, Sweet 'N Low, oil and eggs; mix well.
Blend in flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Serve over sliced cucumbers.

title: chicken pot pie ii
directions: In 2 quart saucepan, heat soup, onion, and bouillon together. Add chicken and vegetables.
Combine this mixture with the potatoes in a 3 quart baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are browned.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup, beans and chili powder.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add water if thinner chili is desired.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix and bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: oostdyk's hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in small saucepan.
Add milk and cook over medium heat until thick.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Cook beef and onion until tender and lightly browned.
Combine with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, salt pepper and chili sauce.
Mix well.
Place in 9x13x2 baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well after each one.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: basic best salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf in a greased pan.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting(food processing)
directions: Mix all together and blend for 1 minute.
Be sure to use a metal blade.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Shuck corn.
Wash and remove silk.
After cutting the kernels in half with a sharp knife, cut kernels off cob.
Scrape juice out of corn cob into the bowl of corn.
Pour bacon fat into a frying pan and heat.
Add corn, stirring in flour, sugar and water.
Let simmer at medium heat until kernels are tender.
Raise heat, stirring at intervals, until brown.
Scrape brown mixture sticking to pan into kernels.
Add salt and pepper.
If necessary, add a little water.
Mixture should be moist.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in Italian dressing overnight.
Cook on grill.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of baking dish.
Put 1/2 package of soup mix over top of rice.
Add water, salt, pepper and pork chops to dish.
Sprinkle with remainder of soup mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: diet jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil the 7-Up and gelatine.
Add the orange juice concentrate. Stir. Add fruit of choice (chopped apples, pineapple with juice, bananas and cantaloupe are all good).

title: chicken supreme
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add rolled chicken breasts.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Remove chicken; stir in soup and sliced mushrooms, mixing well.
Return chicken to skillet; heat for a few minutes more.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and butter, add flour, eggs and cocoa. Mix well, add vanilla and pecans. Pour into large greased pan. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large bowl; use electric mixer and blend well.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in diced apples. Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until taster comes out clean.
Let cake cool 10 minutes in pan on wire rack, then turn out onto rack.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: caesar potato salad
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients with fork until well blended.
Add potatoes, bacon, onion and parsley to mixture.
Toss gently to mix.
Arrange egg slices on top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: hot potato salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the above ingredients, evenly distributing everything for the best taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sesame chicken fingers
directions: In a medium bowl, blend egg, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir in chicken; let stand 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut unpeeled zucchini into bite size pieces.
Parboil about 8 minutes.
Drain well; set in all ingredients with zucchini.
Mix well and set aside.
In separate bowl, mix 1 small package Pepperidge Farm Herb stuffing (just as it comes in package) and 1 stick melted butter or margarine.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, alternate layer of half of stuffing mix, layer of squash mixture. Use remainder of stuffing on top.
Sprinkle paprika and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Note:
This can be made ahead and frozen for future use.
Just heat in 350° oven for 1/4 hour.

title: zucchini and cheese omelet
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Put in frying pan that can also be put in oven and under broiler, preferably an iron one.
Add water, salt and oil and simmer about 15 minutes until zucchini starts to look transparent.
If desired, while zucchini is simmering, add garlic clove sliced lengthwise. Pour off water, oil and garlic, leaving zucchini in pan.
In another bowl, beat eggs, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Dot the zucchini with butter and keep over a low flame.
When butter is melted, add the well-beaten eggs.
Cook over a very low flame until the eggs start to look slightly firm.
The top will still be raw. Spread the cup of grated Mozzarella cheese on top and place the entire pan in a 350° double oven for about 10 minutes.
The whole thing will look messy and gooey.
Remove the pan from oven, sprinkle with Parmesan and place under boiler for about 5 minutes. Remove; cool 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna; add
oil	to
keep
from	sticking.
Cook beef, onion and garlic together over medium flame until brown. Add tomato
paste,
tomatoes,
salt,
pepper
and
basil
and oregano. Cook over
low
flame
until
thickened,	about
15 minutes. Grease 2 1/2 quart casserole and arrange as follows: tomato and meat mixture, Parmesan cheese, noodles, Mozzarella or Ricotta. Repeat
ending
with
meat and Parmesan cheese.** Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend peppers, onion and tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes and pour into jars; seal.

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed and mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: around the house
directions: Pour baking soda in kitchen drain.
Pour vinegar in.
This will bubble and churn.
When bubbling stops, rinse with hot water. Follow with the other baking soda and more hot water.
This will unclog a slow drain and keep the kitchen smelling sweet.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place fresh spinach in large salad bowl.
Sprinkle pine nuts and raisins.
Toss with balsamic vinegar (just enough to lightly coat leaves).
Place chunks of goat cheese on top, then cracked pepper.
Can be made on individual plates or in large bowl.
Serve as first course with Italian bread or along with soups and stews.

title: end of garden pickles
directions: Soak first 5 ingredients in saltwater overnight (1/2 cup salt to 2 qt. water).
Drain.
Cook carrots and green beans in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and boil 10 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once. Keep boiling while packing jars.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and add water to make 1 gallon of punch. Add food coloring to change the color of the punch.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: *Use Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk, not evaporated milk.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange in a greased pan.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces; place on top of broccoli.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat brown sugar, sugar and oil in bowl until well mixed.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and soda; mix well. Stir in apples, walnuts and coconut.
Pour into oiled and floured tube pan or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
May add raisins if desired.
Yields 16 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: In medium skillet, cook and stir ground beef and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce and paste, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
In ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch, alternate layers of meat and sauce, noodles, Swiss cheese, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese, beginning and ending with meat and sauce.
Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before baking.

title: pork and cheese balls
directions: Brown pork and onion until done; drain.
In mixing bowl, add all ingredients; mix well.
Make 1-inch balls; put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin with 1/2 cup of cold water.
Heat soup; add gelatine to soup.
Add cream cheese and mayo in blender until smooth.
Stir in onion, celery and shrimp.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: aunt julia's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Gradually add flour and milk alternately.
Add the vanilla. Makes three 9-inch layers or bake in mold about 1 1/2 hours or longer at 350°.
Test with toothpick.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, green chilies and seasonings in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until hot.

title: candy orange slice bread
directions: Slice candy; mix with 1 cup flour, making sure each piece is dusted.
Add dates.
Cream margarine and eggs.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda together.
Add flour mixture to margarine, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and candy mix.
Pour into 3 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: angel hair pasta with green beans and almonds
directions: Boil a large pot of water.
Toast the almonds in an ungreased skillet.
Saute almonds over medium heat, shaking the pan frequently until lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: green chili
directions: Soak beans 4 to 5 hours.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours; set aside. Cook sausage 2/3 of way done then add all other ingredients except oil and flour; cook 5 to 7 minutes.
In a separate frying pan, put 1/8 cup oil and all of flour to make gravy then put it all together.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: pasta fagioli soup
directions: Saute ground beef.
Drain.
Add everything else and simmer until tender.
Add pasta; cook approximately 15 minutes or until pasta is done.
Recipe makes 5 (2-cup) servings.

title: rocky road pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat on low speed until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Place in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/3 cup peanuts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon mix into pie crust.
Cover with whipped cream and remaining peanuts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding flour last, to make a soft dough.
Roll out flat and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Frost when cooled.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in a loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy green enchiladas(yum-yum)
directions: Combine beef and salt; brown in skillet.
Pour off drippings. Stir in cheese (Cheddar) and onion; set aside.
Combine soup, milk and cheese (Velveeta) in a medium pan; place over low heat.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted; add chiles and set aside.
Fry tortillas in oil.
Spread tortillas with meat mixture.
Roll tight and place in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over tortillas.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chunky tomato sauce
directions: Shred the onions and carrots. Dice the green pepper. Mince the garlic. Peel and dice the tomatoes into a colander to drain.

title: glazed fruit dessert
directions: This may be used by diabetics by using sugar-free instant pudding mix and washing the mandarin oranges in cold water and draining them.
Also, Cool Whip light may be used for the topping.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all; pour into a lightly greased 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.
This can be frozen.
You can substitute broccoli for zucchini.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add sugar, if using fresh cranberries, and mix until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients; chill until set.

title: lemon cookie bars
directions: Mix 10x sugar, flour and margarine like pie dough.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Pour on crust. Bake for 20 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle top with 10x sugar. Let cool and cut into bars.

title: fruit punch for fifty, island style
directions: Combine frozen juices, water and tea in a large punch bowl, stirring well.
Add chilled ginger ale and ice and serve immediately.
Makes over 6 quarts or 50 servings of 1/2-cup each.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Add and mix the egg, margarine and baking powder. Drop by tablespoon onto well oiled hot griddle.
Brown well on one side.
Turn and brown well on other.
Serve at once.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve hot with crackers.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic salt and ginger.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes, gradually adding sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. Fold in dry ingredients. Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 pan. Bake at

375° for 20 minutes. Let cool slightly (5 minutes). Turn onto a towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar (and a little regular sugar on top too). Roll towel and cake together. Cool in the refrigerator.

title: rice casserole
directions: Heat oil and add uncooked rice.
Cook until rice is lightly brown.
Add vegetables and cook until softened.
Add tomatoes, water and spices.
Set heat for simmer.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes in covered pan.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy steamed potatoes
directions: Line pan with foil; leave enough to wrap up potatoes.
Cut potatoes in chunks; place in foil lined pan.
Chop up jalapeno peppers and onions in with potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place dabs of butter around and enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: dynamite
directions: Fry onions and celery together.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer slowly for one hour.
Serve over hot dogs or hamburger rolls.
Makes a large quantity.
Even better when heated the next day.

title: italian bread loaf
directions: Let bread raise and then cut in half.
Roll out half of bread on floured bread board.
Beat egg and brush over rolled out bread and sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Place pepperoni and shredded Mozzarella cheese on top of rolled out bread.
Roll it up like a jelly roll and pinch the edges.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Stir together popcorn, candies and peanuts.
Melt marshmallows, oleo and corn oil.
Mix dry ingredients in with the marshmallow mixture.
Put into well buttered Bundt cake pan or another shape.
Refrigerate 5 minutes.
Tip out onto plate.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Keep in cool place.

title: chocolate toffee crescent bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place on ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Press dough to cover bottom of pan.
Seal together.

title: jello salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese and whip.
Add pecans, pineapple and coconut.
Stir in carton of Cool Whip.
Let set until firm.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook
first 8 ingredients together for about 3 minutes. Let cool.
Add	soda dissolved in 2 tablespoons of warm water. Stir in flour
and baking powder. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at	350°
to 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from Bundt pan to cool.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, drained pineapple and peaches.
Cut peaches in small pieces.
Mix chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix all together.
Pour mixture into the 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add package of taco seasoning and refried beans to hamburger.
Mix and heat thoroughly.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and taco sauce. Spread on top of hamburger mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pineapple; blend well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in pan.
Put in pineapple; top with remainder
of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Cook cranberries in water and sugar until cranberries have all popped open.
Cook 5 minutes longer on simmer.
Pour over package of Jell-O.
Stir and cool until thick.
Add celery, nuts, salt and apples.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Mix melted oleo and brown sugar together in bowl.
Add hot water, egg, and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix well. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 inch pizza pan well.
Flour hands and press dough evenly into pan.
Sprinkle with a selection of toppings from the list below.
Top with 1 cup miniature marshmallows.
Bake about 18 minutes until browned.
Loosen at edges of pan with flexible spatula.
When cool, cut into wedges with pizza cutter.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Layer shrimp and onion rings in casserole or glass bowl.
Mix last 6 ingredients and pour over shrimp and onions.
Refrigerate overnight (will keep 2 months).
Stir occasionally to keep vinegar mixed with oil.
Can be eaten plain or with crackers.
Serves 30!

title: rumaki(appetizer)
directions: Drain chestnuts.
Soak them in soy sauce 2 hours in refrigerator.

(I put leftover soy sauce back in the bottle.) Wrap bacon around each chestnut with toothpick to hold in place. Place on ungreased cookie sheet in oven at 350° until bacon is crispy, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and soda and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix flour, cream of tartar and vanilla with other ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press cookie flat.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: frank's skillet supper
directions: Combine the tomato sauce, the sauce mix, water and green pepper in a large skillet.
Add spaghetti, broken in half.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in franks.
Cover; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, or until spaghetti is tender.
Top with cheese; heat until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tiny timmies(cookies)
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons of the syrup.
Cream sugar, butter and orange rind, add egg and reserved syrup; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add morsels, pineapple and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Garnish with pieces of candied cherries.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: noodle raisin cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and sugars together until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and baking soda; mix lightly. Cover; refrigerate.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix the cheeses.
Brown the beef and drain fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes. Add the seasonings.
Pour about 1 cup meat sauce in the bottom of a 3-quart casserole.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagna over the sauce. Cover with about 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Next, spread 1/2 the cheese mixture over the sauce. Repeat layers of lasagna, sauce and cheese. Top with a layer of lasagna and remaining sauce. Cover with foil and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove the foil and bake 10 minutes longer. Allow to stand about 10 minutes before cutting.

title: creamy vegetable toss
directions: Cook the green beans (Italian-style) according to directions. Rinse and drain.
In a large mixing bowl, combine green beans, squash or zucchini, mushrooms, red or green peppers and green onion.
Stir basil into buttermilk salad dressing.
Add dressing to vegetable mixtures; toss to coat.
Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to set at room temperature for 1 hour.
Mix salad dressing and cream cheese.
Beat well with electric mixer. Add Cheddar cheese and blend.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes. Shape cheese mixture into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in toasted almonds.

title: french boat bread
directions: Cook and drain ground beef, sausage, onion and bell pepper. Take bread out of loaf, leaving a boat.
Mix egg, milk and bread crumbs with meat mixture; then put in boat with cheese on bottom, then meat and cheese.
Put top on, melt butter or margarine and put on top.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato catsup(makes 8 or 9 pints)
directions: Chop tomatoes, pepper and onions.
Squeeze out juice.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Add chopped mixture and cook until color changes.
Pour into jars.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add milk and chocolate and beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, put in crust.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: whoopy cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand except for filling. Stir well. Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour onto pan then sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a clean dish towel and turn cake onto towel.
Peel off waxed paper and roll cake lengthwise on towel and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake pie shell for 5 minutes. Combine sugar and cream cheese. Add sour cream and eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Mix well. Pour into pie crust and bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool. Top with can of pie filling of your choice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans until tender and drain.
Add soup, sour cream and water chestnuts (sliced).
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Put mixture on top of broccoli mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Beat together sour cream, salt, vanilla and egg.
Add apples, mixing carefully to coat well.
Turn into pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: stir-fried garlic shrimp
directions: Cook garlic in oil over medium-high heat for 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Add shrimp; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, onions and wine; cook 2 minutes or until shrimp are pink and vegetables are hot.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pepper jelly
directions: *BLKLIN pans with butter.
The crust will be soft and flaky.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, make stiff batter mixing ingredients in order given (dry ingredients first).
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead a little.
Grease bowl with oil.
Put dough in and turn over so oily side is up.
Cover with cloth or paper and let stand overnight.
Dough rises slowly.
Don't put in refrigerator or too hot a place.
Next morning, punch down and knead a little. Divide into 3 parts; knead each part 8 to 10 times.
Shape into loaves or rolls and place in pans coated with shortening.
Brush with oil and cover with paper or foil.
Let rise 4 to 6 hours or all day is okay if not too hot.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake to 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and brush with butter.
Place on wire rack, covering loaves with cloth until cool.
Serve hot, refrigerate or freeze.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion fine.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Best when sets 2 or 3 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: "la lime delights"
directions: Butter cookie sheet which has an edge.
Measure out the cereal and the peanut butter.
Set aside.
In a large size pan, bring to a boil on medium temperature the corn syrup and sugar. When syrup boils, add peanut butter, then the cereal.
Press onto cookie sheet.
Melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Frost the mix on cookie sheet. cut into bite size squares.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts and chill.
Good with turkey.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Soak breasts in mixture overnight.
Take 2 cups of bread crumbs and roll chicken in them.
Melt butter and drizzle over chicken that has been placed in casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: husbands delight casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain, add tomato sauce and sugar, salt and pepper and simmer for 5 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions (in blender, if possible).
Cook noodles.
Layer in oblong greased casserole.
Put hamburger on bottom, then noodles, then cream cheese, sour cream, onion mixture over noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake casserole for 30 minutes in 350 degree oven. Brown uncovered at 375 degrees.

title: cajun seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a quart jar and use on meat, chicken, vegetables, etc.

title: never-fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk on medium heat until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered oblong cake pan.
Makes 4 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: garlic sticks
directions: Cut buns in quarters lengthwise.
Combine margarine and garlic salt.
Brush sides of buns with mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and seed.
Toast in 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Makes 24 sticks.

title: aunt gertrude's salad dressing
directions: Put in bowl and beat or beat with Mixmaster.
Chill well.

title: reese cups
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter in large bowl.
Work in sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press mixture in 9 x 13 cake pan. Melt chocolate and spread quickly over top.
Chill and cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into a ball.
Put on crackers.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk to egg yolks, then add corn meal mixture.
Add shortening; mix again.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caviar-stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Carefully remove and sieve egg yolks.
Blend butter; carefully stir in caviar and dash of pepper. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 12 halves.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In large saucepan or stockpot, combine hash brown patties and 2 1/2 cups water.
Cover and place over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally to break up patties.

title: homemade bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour with other dry ingredients.
Heat milk, water and butter until very warm.
Mix at low speed.
Gradually pour in liquid ingredients.
Increase to medium speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in 1/2 cup flour for 2 minutes.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth while adding more flour (10 minutes). Place in greased bowl.
Cover with towel for 1 hour.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; roll out half of dough.
Shape in loaf. Place in greased pan.
Cover; set aside both loaves for 1 hour. Pour melted butter over and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.
Remove from pan.

title: potato chowder
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add the diced potatoes. Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Mash part of the potatoes.
Add milk (2 cups).
Cook on low heat for awhile, until thickened.
Stir and watch carefully.
Delicious with a nice piece of bread and salad for a supper.

title: mushroom cream cheese logs
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Mince well.
Blend with cream cheese and seasonings.
Divide among rectangles of crescents.
(Pinch rectangles together.)
Roll up starting at long side.
Cut in 4 equal pieces.
Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain.
Dice celery, cucumber, tomato, onion and green pepper.
Boil eggs until done.
Peel and dice them.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; save.
Clean peppers and core.
Boil tops and peppers in salt water for 5 minutes; drain.

title: cranapana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Fold in cranberries, apples, walnuts and raisins.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients together (nuts optional).
Great for diabetics.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk, beat until well blended.
Add cracker crumbs and set aside until liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese while hot.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Combine ham, pasta, broccoli, salad dressing, milk, red or green pepper and 1 cup cheese in bowl; mix gently.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tight container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mixture for each cup of tea.
Add boiling water.
This can be varied to suit your taste.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in boiling water. Drain blueberries and pine apples catching the juices; add enough water to make 1 c.; add to jello. Stir in blueberries and pineapple. When jello starts to set, pour into a 2 qt. flat pan; refrigerate until set. Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese, and vanilla; spread over jello layer; sprinkle pecans on top. Very sweet and rich. May be served as a dessert.

title: belgian waffles
directions: In a bowl, combine sour cream, melted butter, milk and egg yolks.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir dry mixture into sour cream mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites; do not overmix.

title: not so sweet pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add
eggs,
beat
until fluffy. Make paste of cocoa and vinegar and add to mixture.
Sift salt, soda and flour together;
add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and red food
coloring.
Makes
three
9-inch
layers. Bake at 350°.
Cool layers before icing.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Mix as you would a regular pound cake (add food color before adding flour).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use 10-inch tube pan.

title: open-faced turkey sandwiches
directions: Combine contents of vegetable seasoning packet and water in medium saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup butter and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir until moistened.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Blend in egg.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Spoon stuffing into skillet in 6 mounds; flatten to form thin patties. Brown on one side; turn, spread with relish and top with turkey slices.
Continue cooking to brown second side.
Serve with gravy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon cheese loaf
directions: Drain, bone and flake salmon, add ingredients and mix well. Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot seafood pie
directions: Combine crab meat, shrimp, celery, green peppers, onions, lemon juice, pimientos and mayonnaise in a large bowl; stir well. Spoon mixture into potato crust.
Combine remaining crushed potato chips and cheese.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Process zucchini in food processor.
Do not peel.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Mix well.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to instructions and cool.
Add bell pepper, onions and olives.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving juice.
Chop artichoke hearts and add to rice.
Mix mayonnaise, juice from artichoke hearts and curry powder.
Add to rice and mix well. Refrigerate at least 8 hours and serve cold.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together.
Put 4 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: kentucky fried chicken coleslaw
directions: Mix all really well.
Shred 1 head of cabbage and 1 carrot. Add dressing mixture, mix well and chill at least 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy prune cake
directions: Chop prunes very fine.
Mix together oil and sugar.
Add prunes and liquid.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in milk, then dry ingredients and vanilla. Spread evenly in an 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Microwave for 8 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: marshmallow peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan; add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Add corn syrup or honey and bring to a quick boil. Cook without stirring until when tested in cold water several drops form a soft ball.
Remove from fire and beat until creamy; add peanut butter and stir until thick enough to pour into buttered dish.
Quickly push marshmallows into the mixture, leaving about 1/4-inch between them.
Cut into squares with marshmallows centering the squares.

title: cinnamon crispies
directions: Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes (longer baking time yields crunchier cookies).

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese and eggs.
Place broccoli florets in a 1-quart ovenproof casserole dish.
Top with cheese mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until set. Serves 2.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Sprinkle coconut over cracker crumbs. Sprinkle nuts over coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over nuts. Pour condensed milk over the top of the mixture and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before cutting into squares to serve.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach, according to package directions.
Melt butter. Combine spinach, butter, cream cheese, artichokes and juice of lemon.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it becomes dough-like and pulls away from sides of pan.
Store in Ziploc bag or airtight container.
Makes a soft, pliable play dough for children which will stay soft for years.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil mixture together 5 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Whip 15 minutes.
Very thick.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas.
Arrange bananas, pineapple and strawberries or blueberries in layers over cheese mixture.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and decorate with cherries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Tastes like banana split.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In a bowl, blend together the Bisquick, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Add 2 eggs.
Grate the zucchini and add to the mixture, making a batter.
In a large frypan or pancake griddle, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour batter into pancake size.
Fry 3 minutes on each side. Serve while warm.
Makes 8 to 10 fritters.

title: rocky mountain baked beans
directions: Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours. Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: eggs a la michoacan
directions: Saute onion in 12-inch Dutch oven in bacon grease.
Add enchilada
sauce,
water,
chilies,
oregano and chili powder. Bring
to
a
boil.
Slip unbroken eggs into sauce.
Cover and cook
for
15 minutes.
Spread margarine on tortilla warmed on cast-iron
griddle.
Remove one egg at a time with spatula and place
on tortilla.
Season to taste, top with sauce, top with cheese and sour cream.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Place cottage cheese and pineapple in large bowl.
Add dry gelatin; mix well.
Add whipped topping; mix again.

title: white icing
directions: Cook milk and flour to a paste, but do not boil.
Stir while cooking.
Cool milk and flour mixture.
Beat at high speed remaining ingredients and then add milk and flour mixture and beat thoroughly.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and
butter;
add
eggs,
milk and vanilla. Add flour, salt and
baking powder.
Mix all well.
Add fruit, which has been mixed with
1/2 cup of the flour.
Add nuts and coconut. Grease and flour 4
loaf
pans.
Bake
at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach appetizer
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and chill.
Carve out middle of rye bread and scoop dip into center.
Serve with cut-up pieces of rye bread from center.

title: chocolate nut toffee
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, cream and salt in saucepan.
Place over low flame and cook to 244° (use candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Add butter and continue cooking until a small amount of mixture forms a hard ball in cold water (254°).
Remove from fire; add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan (8 x 8-inch); cool.
Pour melted chocolate over toffee.
Let stand until cold. Remove from pan and break into small irregular pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pans.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine together and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and nuts. Pour on top of first mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes or more.
This makes a lot and it is nice to have some extra in freezer for company.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter in a large heavy saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and add sugar, blending well. Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in flour and vanilla. Add marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts and mix thoroughly. Turn mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until mostly set. Cool in pan. Cut into squares to serve. Makes 24 brownies.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together by shaking in a tightly sealed jar.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with dried beef. Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Place on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 225° for 3 hours.

title: aunt sammye's peking roast
directions: Cut slits completely through the meat.
Insert slivers of garlic and onion into slits.
Place brisket in bowl and pour 1 cup of vinegar over it.
Be sure vinegar gets into slits.
Soak 24 to 48 hours in refrigerator.
When ready to cook, pour off vinegar. Brown in heavy pot in small amount of cooking oil until almost burned on both sides.
Pour 2 cups of strong black coffee over roast.
Add 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer on top of stove for 6 hours.
Twenty minutes before serving, add salt and pepper.
(You may use 1/2 cup of gin or whiskey to boiling mixture.)

title: mexican corn bread casserole with meat
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and pepper.
Set this mixture aside.
Combine eggs, milk and 1 cup corn with corn bread mix.
Pour half the batter into a 9-inch greased pan.
Top with mixture, cheese slices and the remaining cup of corn.
Pour the rest of the batter on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
