Put a layer of avocado mix in about an 8-inch bowl, then a layer of cheese until you use it all.

title: pecan pie(southern style)
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, melted oleo and syrup. Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: whole lemon pie
directions: Wash lemon, slice and cube.
Use rind, but remove seeds.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Process well at high speed.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine fruits, pecans and marshmallows.
Blend egg yolks, mustard, salt and lemon juice; cook until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over fruit mixture; let stand overnight. Serve on lettuce.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with some grated cheese.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish; cover with some more grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mrs. wenzel's ikes cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Cool cocoa and water mix.
Add egg yolks and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add cooled cocoa.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternating with sour milk or buttermilk in 1/3's.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn batter into 2 greased and floured pans. Bake approximately 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Frost with my favorite buttercream frosting.

title: pepper steak
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak and cut into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle meat with paprika; allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter. Add garlic and broth.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover; cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture, stirring until clear and thickened (about 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes and stir.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: daddy's dunkers
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then cream and vanilla. Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pinch into 1-inch balls and press with flour-dipped tines of fork onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° just until edges are light brown.
Don't brown whole cookie.

title: supper in the skillet
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion.
Combine all ingredients in a deep skillet; cover and cook over a low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cook until tender.

title: oatmeal banana muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together sugar and butter or margarine. Beat in eggs, banana and honey.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, beating just until blended.
Stir in oats.
Fill 24 muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Kids love'em.

title: corn pudding
directions: A full-bodied potato casserole makes the perfect partner for just about any dish, whether it be beef, poultry or fish.
This one is fortified with cream cheese, eggs and ham to give it a slight smoky flavor and spiced with exotic cumin, turmeric and cayenne.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
In small bowl, combine cheese, sugar, salt, basil and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add dressing to vegetables.
Toss gently.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add bacon.
You can also add 1 head of lettuce, torn into bite-size pieces, 2 cups seasoned croutons and 8 ounce can sliced water chestnuts, drained just before serving.
Makes 20 to 24 servings with lettuce.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown in large skillet the ground beef, mushrooms, garlic powder, onion and water. stir often. Keep heat low.
Add flour, salt, pepper, cream of mushroom soup and water. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook pasta until al dente and drain.
Cut chicken into strips. Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and stir for 1 minute.
Add broccoli and saute for 2 minutes, then transfer to a heated dish.
Add chicken to the skillet and saute until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Toss pasta with broccoli and chicken.
Garnish with parsley.
Sprinkle with pepper and serve.

title: confetti casserole(great company dish!)
directions: Saute onion and peppers; add soup, milk and cheese.
Simmer until all cheese is melted.
Chop up broccoli and mix with rice into cheese mixture.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish. Bake until bubbly at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and 4 cups milk in double boiler until done.
Beat egg yolks and add 4 cups heated milk and cornstarch.
Add this mixture to rice in double boiler.
Pour in casserole and place in a pan of warm water.
Bake in a moderate oven (325° to 350°) until a silver knife comes out clean.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan before removing from pan.

title: watermelon cookies
directions: Beat butter and shortening in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beat well.
Stir in egg, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add a small amount of red food coloring to color dough as desired, beating until blended.
Shape dough into balls, cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Divide dough in half; store one portion in refrigerator. Roll remaining portion to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut dough with 3 inch cookie cutter; cut circle in half. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press several chocolate mini-morsels in each cookie.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (do not brown).
Cool on wire racks.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut up crab meat to bite-size pieces.
Add celery, onion and olives to crab.
Mix oil, vinegar, dill weed and capers (also salt and pepper).
Toss with crab, then add mayonnaise and blend.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, melt 1/2 stick of butter. Make sure melted butter gets up on the edges.
Place crushed pineapple in bottom of dish.
Next, put a layer of cherry pie filling.
Top the two layers with cake mix.
Melt remaining butter and drizzle butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add green onion and horseradish.
Stir in flaked fish.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve as a dip with crackers or Melba toast. Excellent spread on toasted bread rectangles and garnish as desired with parsley sprigs or pimento diamonds.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups dip.

title: shrimp teriyaki
directions: Marinate shrimp in juice, soy sauce and oil for 20 minutes. Drain and broil shrimp 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with rice. Serves 6.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In large bowl, layer cubed cake, pudding, Cool Whip, strawberries (if desired), and crushed candy bar, ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with crushed candy bar and sliced strawberries (if desired).

title: mike's pot roast
directions: Coat both sides of pot roast with flour and brown in butter in an electric frying pan and turn temperature to low.
Fill pan with water to top edge of meat.
Generously sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and chargrilled seasoning and then coat top of meat with horseradish.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, adding water so water doesn't completely evaporate.
Flip meat; add carrots and onion and simmer 20 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Serve when meat is tender and gravy is desired consistency.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Put chicken in casserole. Spread apricot jam over the chicken. Sprinkle Russian Dressing over the chicken, then the dry soup mix over top. Bake at 325 for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: santa fe tuna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on box.
Add tuna or chopped chicken and frozen vegetables and simmer until hot.

title: date cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add egg yolks and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan; cover with chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; add 1 cup brown sugar and dates.
Fold gently; pour over chocolate chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ravioli primavera casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook ravioli according to package directions.

title: tostadas(baked casserole)
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef.
Add the taco mix and water and simmer to evaporate liquid.
Add the refried beans and tomato sauce and heat through.
Place a tortilla in your baking dish and spread with meat sauce.
Sprinkle black olives, green onions, cheese and chilies to taste.
Repeat until meat sauce is gone or your baking dish is full, whichever comes first, usually 3-4 layers.
Spread the top of the last tortilla top with butter. Bake at 350° until top is brown.
Serve with a variety of toppings like salsa, chopped tomato, chopped lettuce, avocado slices, and sour cream, or your family favorites.
Serves 4-6.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in 30 cup percolator and heat.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: citrus marinated shrimp
directions: In saucepan, combine lemon slices, bay leaves, water, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and boil, covered, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain shrimp in colander, refresh under cold water.

title: pork and sausage
directions: Place meat in a baking dish.
Peel and cut into chunks, potatoes and squash.
Place on top of meat.
Peel and slice onions and carrots.
Place on top of other mixture.
Dab with spaghetti sauce (homemade or store bought).
Dab here, there and everywhere. Bake for 3 to 4 hours, covered, at 300°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg. Then add bread crumbs.
Pour into glass 2-quart casserole pan or bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until firm and golden brown.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add 2 cups of sugar and continue beating.
Add the four eggs and beat until mixture is very creamy. Preheat oven to 325°.
To mixture add vanilla and lemon juice and continue mixing well.
In a small bowl add baking soda, baking powder and salt to one cup of flour.
Add to mixture; beat about 2 minutes.
Add the rest of flour, one cup at a time.
Mixture will be a little stiff.
Add sour cream and continue beating until mixture is creamy.
Oil and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, a Bundt pan or a cheesecake pan.
Add 1/2 of cake mixture to the baking pan and smooth it out.
In a cup mix 1/2 cup of sugar with cinnamon. Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Spoon remaining batter over the sugar-cinnamon and spread evenly.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon/sugar mixture on top of the cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: samantha's famous raspberry pie
directions: Prepare crust.
Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and almond extract.
Gently stir in berries.
Pour into crust; dot with margarine.
Cover with other crust; trim overhanging.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain 1 can and 1/2 of other can of corn.
Melt together cream cheese, oleo and milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: miracle lasagne
directions: Spray 11 x 7-inch dish with cooking spray.
If using ground beef, brown, drain and mix with sauce.
In baking dish spread 1 cup sauce (if using ground beef use a little more sauce mixture).
Top with 3 dry noodles, half of the Ricotta cheese, half of the Mozzarella and half of the Parmesan.
Top that with 1 cup sauce. Repeat with noodles and cheese.
Top with remaining sauce.
Slowly pour 1/4 cup (or less) water around inside edge of dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: deer or beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into strips (thickness of a cigarette, remove fat). Put strips in sauce.
Soak overnight in refrigerator; cover.
Stir occasionally.
Drain.
Lay meat out; pat with paper towel.
Lay on racks.
Place racks on cookie sheets.
Place in oven at lowest heat.
Dry 4 to 8 hours.
You can also put foil on racks and just lay meat on that instead of cookie sheets.

title: corn soup
directions: Saute grated onion in butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and corn.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish each bowl with chopped parsley.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Melt fat in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and Minute rice (right from the package).
Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve it steaming, and sit back for applause from four muchos happy people.

title: egg rice bake
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add mushroom soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Stir rice into remaining mixture.
Put in a greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise; press the halves into rice mixture. Drizzle reserved soup mixture over eggs and cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes and put in colander to drain.
Cut the onions and peppers into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and boil on low for 1/2 hour.
Stir constantly.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: In 1 quart saucepan melt butterscotch chips on low heat, stirring constantly until smooth (3 to 5 minutes).
Pour into large mixer bowl; add all other ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping sides of bowl often, until well mixed.
Divide dough in half; wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until firm (1 hour).
Heat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured surface roll out dough, half at a time to 1/8 inch.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly brown. Cool.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel potatoes and cook until tender.
Peel and chop onion.
Cut pepper into strips.
Slice green beans.
Dice celery.
Finely chop garlic.
Mix all together with parsley.
In large skillet, brown ground meat and drain.
Add vegetables and vinegar to meat; cook few minutes.
Mash potatoes, nutmeg, milk and butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Put meat and vegetables in lightly greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Top with potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until potatoes are light brown.
Takes about 90 minutes start to stop.

title: crabby muffins
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Spread on English muffins (each muffin cut into 6 wedges).
Freeze on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Place in plastic bags and freeze until ready to use. Just before serving, broil until bubbly and crisp.
Serve hot.

title: lazy daisy cake(only 1 tablespoon fat)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour 3 or 4 times after adding baking powder and salt.
Sift flour mixture into egg mixture and beat well.
Heat milk; add butter, then add to egg and flour.
Beat well and pour into well greased pan; bake slowly about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken indienne
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Brown chicken.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add lemon juice, chicken stock, mincemeat, salt, pepper, rice and curry powder.
Mix. Put in buttered dish.
Arrange chicken over it. Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan balls
directions: Combine ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Form into balls.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool; roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pork loin roast
directions: Combine sage, pepper and salt.
Rub over pork roast.
Place roast fat side up on rack in open pan.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix
with
electric
mixer and chill for several hours. Spoon into muffin tins and bake at 425° until brown.

title: vinegar and oil salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container with a lid.
Shake before each use.
Chill.
Great on salads.

title: skillet shrimp scampi
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil. Add shrimp and marinade. Cook, stirring often, until shrimp turns pink. Stir in green onions. Turn heat off. Serve over hot cooked rice or your favorite pasta.

title: apricot crisp
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Bring to boil in saucepan.
Thicken with cornstarch and cold water mixed together. Cook several minutes, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Arrange apricot halves in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over apricots and top with granola.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: ham and noodles
directions: Mix butter, flour and milk to make white sauce.
Add cheese. Alternate layers of ham, noodles and sauce in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and vanilla.
Stir into first mixture.
Add butter.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites (gradually add 1/3 cup of sugar and 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar).
Beat mixture until stiff.
Pile whites on pie.
Spread and seal edges.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: angel delite
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Add drained pineapple and bananas.
Tear cake up into small pieces and mix with the pudding and fruit.
Top with Cool Whip and chill overnight or at least 6 to 8 hours.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for
15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: mom's foolproof divinity
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt and water in a large saucepan.
Cook without stirring to 248° on candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour half of hot syrup mixture into egg whites while beating at top speed.
Reduce the mixer speed to slow.
Return syrup mixture to heat, cook to 272°. Pour syrup over the whites and beat at top speed until it begins to hold shape. Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon dipped in water.

title: corn relish
directions: Chop tomato into bite size.
Chop onion very small.
Drain corn.
Combine all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Refrigerate overnight or at least two hours.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: In a wok or skillet, saute steak and onions in vegetable oil until meat is well browned and onions are tender.
Add peppers and mushrooms; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes until vegetables are tender. Combine remaining ingredients together in a bowl and add to beef and vegetable mixture.
Stir and cook until sauce thickens, about 2 to 3 more minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip until well mixed. Serve with strawberries and enjoy.

title: cocoa bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in.
Spread in greased oblong pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, frost with butter frosting.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry wreaths
directions: In medium bowl, combine milk, coconut and drink mix.
Cover, chill well.
Using about 1 tablespoon for each, shape into Christmas wreaths and Christmas trees.
If desired, decorate with gold or silver dragees.

title: biscuit sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper; drain well.
Combine eggs, cheese and sausage.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Press biscuits into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour sausage mixture into biscuits lined pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until quiche is set and crust is deep golden brown.
Serve 8 people.

title: sausage strata(used at sunrise breakfast)
directions: Place torn or diced small bread pieces in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute the chopped onion and green pepper in the margarine for 3 minutes.
Add the ground beef and brown the meat while breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.
Add the seasoned salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in the tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat the mixture to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken walnut salad
directions: Place chicken onto a sheet tray and cook in oven at 350° until fully cooked.
Chill the chicken. Cook the pasta until soft. Toss cooked pasta with small amount of olive oil and chill.
Do not rinse.
Dice the onion and celery and reserve.
Wash and pick grapes and reserve. Toast the walnuts and reserve.

title: million dollar chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to wet mixture.
Add chips, nuts and chocolate bar.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until chilled.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased baking sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: pluckets
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, shortening and salt to the scalded milk.
When lukewarm, add dissolved yeast and eggs. Gradually add to flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Stir down and let rise again until doubled.
Stir together the last 3 ingredients.
Take rounded teaspoons of dough and dip into melted butter; roll in sugar-cinnamon-nut mixture. Pile balls loosely in ungreased angel food pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
When baked, turn upside-down immediately.
The rolls will be stuck together and are served that way, letting each one pluck off one or two.

title: hamburger macaroni
directions: Cook ground beef, chopped green pepper, chopped onion and tomato sauce until well done. Add cooked macaroni and grated cheese. Serve hot.

title: salad dressing
directions: Whip together.
Pour over lettuce salad or use for cole slaw.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in strips.
In saucepan, combine beef, gravy and onion.
Cook until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Stir some of hot mix into sour cream.
Return sour cream to meat mix. Cook until heated through and serve over noodles.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.

Stir together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Add oats, chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
In bacon grease, fry onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Fry sausage; drain off fat.
Add beans, onion and pepper.
Simmer while cooking rice.
Put cooked rice in bottom of casserole dish, then add sausage mixture.
Crumble bacon on top.
Can put in oven to keep warm.

title: light and fruity sangria
directions: Day before serving:
In each compartment of two ice-cube trays, place one strawberry, hull side up.
Pour in enough wine to fill each compartment;
freeze.

title: see's fudge candy
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, chocolate chips, oleo or butter, nuts and vanilla together and set aside.
Mix sugar and milk.
Cook at a rolling boil for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over other mixture and stir until chocolate chips are melted.
Pour in a buttered pan and put in refrigerator for 30 minutes before cutting.
Makes 4 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill. Serve with chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain chicken and chop real small; add the rest of the ingredients and serve on regular bread or toasted bun.

title: punch
directions: In a large container, combine slightly thawed juices and pineapple juice.
Mash bananas in blender with water and sugar, and as blended, add to juices.
Mix thoroughly.
Freeze this base in quart containers.
Thaw base a couple hours before needed and add 2 quarts cold ginger ale to 1 quart base.
Each quart mixed with ginger ale serves 20 punch sized servings generously.
Yields approximately 5 quarts.

title: bar cookies
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar.
Add
eggs and beat.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts.	Mix and spread in a 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Do not overcook.

title: senor chicken
directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut in large chunks.
Place tortillas as in package in the bottom of 14 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange other ingredients in layers in this order:
tortillas, chicken, onion, green chiles, combined soup and broth mixture and cheese slices.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tangy sour cream dip
directions: Combine sour cream with other ingredients and stir gently until blended.
Serve with crisp crackers or potato chips.

title: fruit smoothies
directions: Add fruit, yogurt, sugar or honey to a blender. Blend until smooth, if it is too thick, add milk to your desired consistency. Serve in cups or freeze into popsicles.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Test until set.
Save 2 tablespoons cheese for the top.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large frying pan, cook and stir ground beef with onion in butter until onion is tender. Stir in flour, salt, garlic powder, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in soup. Cook an additional 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over boiled noodles.

title: raisin crunch balls
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add marshmallows.
Cook over very low heat, stirring until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over mixed raisins, peanuts and cereal.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Place on tray.
Refrigerate about 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix milk and oats together and let stand.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to the mixture.
Grease pan and fry. Top with butter and Mrs. Butterworths syrup.

title: country-time carrot bread
directions: Cook carrots according to package directions. Place carrots in blender; grate coarsely. Do not puree. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugars, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir together carrots, oil, eggs, water and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients and stir until well blended. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes. Cool.

title: original toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Generously butter bottom of deep pie pan.
Cover bottom of pie pan with miniature marshmallows.
Mix cake mix according to package and pour over marshmallows.
Cut up and mash strawberries and add (dry) jello to this.
When mixed well, pour on top of cake mix.
Marshmallows will come to top during baking, berries will go to bottom.

title: french waffles
directions: Can use use other flavors as desired.

title: grandma schievelbein's sweet rice
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, salt and rice.
Boil rice for about 25 minutes or until water has cooked down.
Add the milk and continue boiling for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the evaporated milk and sugar.
Boil until rice is very thick (approximately 15 minutes), stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chips and margarine in microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add Eagle Brand and mix well.
Add flour and vanilla and mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy kiss, covering completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and appear shiny, but become firm as they cool.
Do not overbake.
Can drizzle melted white chocolate over baked cookies.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put into baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.

title: beef-pork barbecue
directions: Cook in slow cooker all day; last hour of cooking, remove cover.
Remove meat from cooker; cool and shred.
Add barbecue sauce.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out thin. Cut strips 1-inch wide and 4-inches long. Take strips and drop into boiling chicken broth for 15 minutes or until done.

title: cantonese chow mein
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and brown meat.
Push meat to 1 side of skillet and add garlic and onions; saute until soft. Season with salt.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and chicken broth and add to skillet.
Stir and cook until mixture thickens.
Add chow mein vegetables and heat through.
Serve with chow mein noodles or fried rice.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease, add 1 pkg. taco seasoning mix and a couple teaspoons water.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl add lettuce, hamburger, green peppers, onions, tomatoes, cheese, Doritos, toss all together and pour taco sauce over salad and mix well.

title: shrimp fajitas
directions: Blend first seven ingredients together, except tortillas, then add shrimp.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: *Optional:
Use only onions for less salt.

title: strawberry daiquiri pie
directions: Mix together daiquiri mix, Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Divide and spoon into graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate 1 hour or until set.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion until soft in hot (not too hot) oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker toffee bars
directions: Place crackers in jelly roll pan, end to end.
Mix the butter and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil, cooking for 1 1/2 minutes. Add nuts.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until this bubbles.
Cool; remove and break into smaller crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, peanut butter, flour and vanilla.
Add a little more flour.
Form into balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes.

title: never fail brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and Crisco together.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix flour and butter; add nuts and press into bottom of cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: little nothings
directions: Spread preserves over each slice of bread.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Tightly wrap each bread roll in plastic wrap. Chill for several hours or overnight.
Combine pancake mix, sugar and nutmeg; mix well.
Add egg and milk, mixing until smooth.
Dip each bread roll into batter.
Deep-fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve warm with additional preserves or marmalade, if desired. Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baked stuffed scallops
directions: Mix Ritz crackers, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add the cracker mixture. Fold in scallops; mix well.
Place in an ungreased 4-quart casserole dish.
Place heavy cream evenly over top of scallops. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry shortcake ala greg
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar.
Place in refrigerator for at least one hour.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; set aside.
Add gelatin to boiling water and stir for 2 minutes.

title: 3 bean baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion together.
Combine all and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken livers and wild rice
directions: Saute livers and onions in butter about 10 minutes.
Cook rice by directions on box.
Add rice to livers and onions.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered, in 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, and place in a buttered baking dish.
Put crushed potato chips on top and bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions in one half of the oleo until tender in large soup pan.
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, 1 teaspoon salt and water.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes. In another saucepan, melt remaining oleo and add flour, pepper, salt and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add bouillon cubes.
Add to vegetable mixture and simmer. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: grilled ranch bread
directions: Combine butter and dressing mix.
Spread this mixture on bread.
Place bread under broiler until crispy and golden brown.

title: cheese pie
directions: On low burner heat in saucepan cream cheese, powdered sugar and canned milk until mixes, don't boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour mixture in pie crust; top with whole halves of pecans.
Put in freezer for 24 hours.
Take out of freezer and put thawed Cool Whip on top of filling.
Add blueberry (or any pie filling) to top of pie and place back in freezer until ready to eat.
Can be served frozen or slightly thawed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs separately.
Mix all other ingredients; add eggs and beat 4 minutes.
Place into three small bread pans or two larger ones.
Sprinkle small amount of poppy seed on top.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: snickers cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan, reserving the rest.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels.
Add margarine and milk; stir to blend.
Pour caramel mixture over the baked cake.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Spoon the reserved cake batter over all.
Reduce oven to 250° and bake cake for 20 minutes.
Return oven temperature to 350° and bake and additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: eula savoie's squash casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Add seasoning and saute until soft.
Add tomatoes, soup and bread crumbs.
Mix with cooked squash.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bean and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in beans, soup and seasoning.
Bring to boil; pour in casserole.
Top with biscuits and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender but still crisp; cool.
Slice in thin rounds.
Alternate carrots, chopped green pepper and chopped onion in bowl.
Pour sauce over and marinate for several days in refrigerator.
Keeps several weeks.

title: refried beans(makes about 3 cups)
directions: Pick over beans.
Rinse under cold running water.
Combine beans with water to cover in a large kettle.
Bring to boiling; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour.

title: sweet 'n spicy popcorn
directions: Spray a cold 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add popcorn.
Stir together remaining ingredients and add to popcorn.
Toss until coated.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Transfer to a large piece of foil and stir completely. Makes 6 (3/4 cup) servings.
Contains 76 calories, 16 grams carbohydrates, 1 gram fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy in mixing bowl.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix well.
Add zucchini, flour, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Divide batter into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend sugar, pumpkin and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients, sifted.
Stir until well blended.
May use as a drop or bar cookie.
Bake at 375°.

title: charlie's cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a 10-inch frypan (greased).
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Add sugar to beaten egg whites; beat again until thick. Combine all ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop cookies on foil (no pan).
Put in oven and turn oven off.
Leave overnight.
Make at night and don't peek.

title: french chocolates
directions: Combine condensed milk, chocolate and salt in heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat until mixture is quite thick and chocolate is melted, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill several hours.
Drop by teaspoon onto chopped nuts.
Shape into balls and coat with nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato and kielbasa gratin
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, cover the potatoes with 2 inches salted water; bring the water to a boil and simmer the potatoes, covered, for 10 minutes.
Drain and let cool.
Peel the potatoes and grate them.
In a heavy skillet, cook the onions in 4 tablespoons butter over moderate heat, stirring, until it is softened; add the garlic and kielbasa and cook the mixture, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Transfer the mixture to a bowl and combine it well with the potatoes, salt and pepper; spread it in a buttered 3-quart casserole or gratin dish.
In a small bowl, beat together the eggs, milk, cream, nutmeg, salt and pepper and pour over the potato mixture.
Sprinkle with the bread crumbs and cheese; dot with the remaining butter and bake the gratin in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until it is puffed and golden brown.

title: april's little hands pizza
directions: Saute onion and celery in lard until browned.
Stir in flour and salt and slowly add water.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, peas, vinegar, sugar, shrimp and chili powder.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Place rice in a large, deep serving plate and pour Creole mixture over it.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and mash.
Saute onions, garlic and margarine in skillet.
Add sour cream, milk, salt and pepper to taste to mashed potatoes with onion mixture.
Place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, uncovered.
Garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain thoroughly the broccoli and cauliflower.
Chop and break into fine pieces.
Add chopped onion.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Toss well and keep chilled. Very good.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch (jelly roll) pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marbled effect.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: low-fat pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package and drain.
Cook sausage in skillet, stirring frequently, until no longer pink and then drain.
Mix ingredients except cheese in ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake about 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and set aside.
Spray frying pan with Pam.
Pat out hamburger into patties (about 3); put in pan and cook.
When about half done, turn burgers over and put sliced onion on top and cook until burgers are done and onions are tender.
Serve with rice and garden peas (or any vegetable you like).

title: jefferds brothers' steamed penn cove mussels
directions: Place all ingredients but mussels in large saucepan over high heat and bring to boil.
Once boiling, add mussels and cover pan. Steam 5 to 6 minutes or until shells are open.
Remove from heat, discard any unopened shells and ladle mussels and nectar into large bowls.
Serve with French bread, green salad and white wine.

title: easy bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix vinegar and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions and boil 2 minutes longer.
Place vegetables in sterilized jars and seal with regular Mason lids.
Close tightly and let sit for 2 weeks.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, carrots and relish.
Stir in mayonnaise. Top with potatoes, sprinkled on top.
May use French fried onions instead of potatoes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ditalini and bean soup
directions: Heat oil; saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Stir in tomatoes, water, bouillon, carrots, celery, basil, parsley and pepper.
Cook for about 1 hour, until carrots are soft.
Add cannellini; bring to a boil.
Add pasta; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until pasta is tender.
Serve with Italian bread or bread sticks.

title: enchilada casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until done.
Make gravy of the margarine, flour, water, tomato juice and chili powder.
Heat tortillas in gravy.
Place a layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle with meat and grated cheese.
Alternate layers of tortillas, meat and cheese until all is used.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Can be made in the crock-pot or microwave.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Beat together butter, sugar, egg and orange rind until fluffy. Stir in pineapple and 1 tablespoon juice.
Cut pound cake into 4 layers.
Spread 1/4 of filling on each slice of cake; stack each slice of cake on top of another.
Sprinkle coconut over top layer. Wrap in foil and chill.
Cut into slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add soda to persimmon pulp. Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, then add soda and persimmon mixture. Add pecans. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or if using 2 small loaf pans, bake for 1 hour.

title: aunt martha craver's yeast rolls
directions: Melt butter in water.
Add yeast to warm water.
Add liquid mixture to flour and salt.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise 1 time.
Work down.
Turn over.
Let rise again.
Make into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 400°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, stir until mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add margarine or butter.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: You will need a griller.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onions in butter.
Add water, bouillon, salt, pepper and garlic powder and bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve bouillon. Gradually add noodles and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cook 4 minutes.
Add milk and cheese and continue cooking until cheese is melted and soup is hot.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter with chocolate (microwave 8 seconds).
Add sugar and milk and mix.
Frost cookies as needed.
(Used for Italian Chocolate Cookies.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onion and zucchini until tender.
Add to remaining ingredients, except butter and Stove Top.
Mix together and place in bottom of dish, leaving enough to cover top of casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: good neighbors cookies
directions: Drop by spoon.
Make into little balls.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Take green food coloring and almond slices in a small plastic bag and shake until green.
Put aside.
Mix walnut, coconut, Jell-O and milk together and put in freezer for 1 hour.
Take mixture out of freezer and take about 1 teaspoon and roll into balls.
Then roll balls into crystal candy.
Then shape into strawberries.
Then stick a colored almond slice for the stem of the strawberry.
Makes about 36 to 40 strawberries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pankaken
directions: In blender, whisk eggs with a little milk; add flour and remaining ingredients.
Whisk again.
Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan in hot oven.
Pour mixture into melted butter; return to oven.
Cook 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking for 20 minutes.
Serve immediately with:
honey, syrup, peanut butter, strawberries, etc.

title: pierogies
directions: Filling #1: Whipped potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans and drain well.
Pour into dish and pour soup over. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375 for 30-35 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: shoe peg casserole
directions: Mix corn, beans, sour cream, cream of celery soup, green onions, Cheddar cheese and salt.
Put in a baking dish.
Cover top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° until crackers brown, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt dorothy's banana pudding
directions: With a fork, mix yolks and sugar, then mix in flour.
Stir well.
Add vanilla, milk and dash of salt.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine with all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat and cook until thick.

title: egg bake
directions: Beat eggs, add milk and mustard; mix well.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread and sausage in pan.
Pour milk over.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: salami
directions: First day:
Mix together (knead as bread).
Put in bowl, cover and refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Place all the ingredients in mixing bowl.
Do not use mixer. Combine all ingredients with large spoon until well mixed.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern sole
directions: Melt butter over low heat in large skillet, add fish, turning so each piece is well buttered.
Salt and pepper to taste, cover pan tightly and cook over very low heat until fish flakes easily, 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove to a heated platter and keep warm while preparing sauce.

title: instant potato candy
directions: Combine the potato flakes and water in a mixing bowl.
Beat until the mixture holds together and looks like thick mashed potatoes.
Start adding the confectioners' sugar, a cup at a time, and continue adding until the mixture can be formed into a ball. Roll the mixture out to a rectangle about 12 x 8 inches.
Spread the peanut butter over the potato mixture.
Roll up like a jelly roll, starting with the 12 inch side.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into slices about 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces.
Dip pieces into milk.
Coat with flour.
Dip into egg, then into flour again.
Drop into deep fat heated to 350°.
Fry for 20 to 25 minutes, depending on size of pieces.
Drain well.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: strata di pizza
directions: In medium bowl with fork or whisk, beat eggs just until blended.
Beat in tomato sauce, water, oregano, basil, salt and garlic powder; set aside.
In greased 8 or 9-inch square baking dish, arrange 4 slices of bread.
Evenly pour on half the tomato mixture.
Sprinkle with half the Mozzarella.
Repeat layers; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover; let stand at least 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until puffed and browned.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot candy
directions: In a heavy, 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, apricots, butter and salt.
Over medium heat, stirring occasionally, cook to soft ball stage (234° to 240°).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff enough to knead.
Turn out onto board.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into 4 rolls each and store in refrigerator.
To serve, cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: aunt eva's tea cakes
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients together in saucepan until thoroughly blended.
Cool and add cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kahului kalua pork
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Rub liquid smoke and salt into pork. Place long sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Lay Ti leaves in the middle. Place 1 package laulau leaves on top.
Place pork on top and cover with rest of laulau leaves.
Bring Ti leaves up; add more to completely cover pork.
Bring foil up to hold all in place.
Add foil enough to make a totally sealed bundle.
Bake in covered pan for 1/2 hour at 500°.
Reduce temperature to 325° and cook 4 more hours.
Shred and serve with juices.
Serve laulau leaves around edge of platter.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet.
Add peppers, carrots and garlic.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce.
Add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar and ginger.
Bring to a full boil.
Serve chicken over prepared rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° about 40 minutes in a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Prepare Betty Crocker mashed Potato Buds for 8 servings, except decrease salt to 1/2 teaspoon and add 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt.
Stir parsley and cheese into potatoes.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: spicy lasagna
directions: Brown ground turkey with onion and pepper.
Drain Ro-Tel and add to turkey along with tomato paste.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles until done.
Drain, set aside.
Mix eggs with cottage cheese.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture, meat mixture and Velveeta cheese.
Repeat everything except Velveeta.
Bake 30 minutes on 350°.
Add Velveeta to top and bake 15 more minutes.

title: vegetable mix
directions: Cook frozen mixed vegetables with salt.
Drain and let cool. Mix sugar, vinegar and cooking oil.
Mix with vegetables and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Combine chicken and onion.
In a saucepan, slowly warm cream of chicken soup; add sour cream, garlic salt, picante sauce, green chilies and half of the cheese.
Fill flour tortillas with chicken mixture and spoon sauce over; roll.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover last 5 minutes and top with cheese.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Split muffins and toast briefly in toaster, just enough to dry them a bit, then arrange on baking sheet (broiler-proof) as many as you need.
Put about a tablespoon of sauce on each muffin half; sprinkle with cheese and other ingredients.
Put in boiler until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Stir together with rice, thawed broccoli, milk and soup.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 11-inch baking dish; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: lynn's orange ambrosia
directions: Drain oranges very well.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows. Add oranges.
Save a few to decorate on top.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, Karo syrup and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour on top.
Refrigerate.

title: salsa
directions: In mixing bowl thoroughly combine tomatoes, chili peppers and onions.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Let mixture stand at least 30 minutes at room temperature.
Store in refrigerator. Serve as a relish or a dip for tortilla chips.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter together until a soft ball stage. Add dates and heat until the dates are melted.
Remove from fire and add nuts.

title: crab and rice
directions: Fry crab meat and onion in oil until tender.
Add rice, stir; add thyme, allow to cook slowly, stirring occasionally.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in rest of ingredients except sesame seed.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough into ropes the diameter of cigars.
Cut at a slant into 2-inch pieces.
Dip into beaten egg and roll in sesame seed.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes in a 350° oven on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, saute garlic in oil for about 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, 2 Tbsp. chili powder and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix yogurt, chilis, green onions and remaining 1 Tbsp. chili powder in mixing bowl.
Soften tortillas in microwave.
Spoon 1/4 c. tomato sauce into 8-inch baking pan. Spoon yogurt mixture onto tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheeses and roll up.
Place seam side down in prepared pan.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut carrots in thin slices, turnips in small dice and shred beans thinly.
Add all vegetables to stock; gently simmer until vegetables are tender, adding hot water if soup becomes too thick. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crisp crackers or croutons.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar for 12 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add Certo and stir.
Let stand 10 minutes or more.
Pour into baby food jars.

title: kraut with brown sauce
directions: Rinse kraut well in cold water; drain.
Add brown sugar and caraway seed and mix well with fork.
Let stand at room temperature while making brown sauce.
Add 3/4 cup of brown sauce to kraut; mix well.
Put in 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Dot with oleo. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes.

title: seafood and angel hair pasta
directions: Stir-fry all vegetables for about 5 minutes.
Add seasonings, spices and wine.
Boil pasta according to directions on box; drain.
Put drained pasta into seafood mixture.
Serve while still hot.

title: spud 'n 'sparagus soup
directions: In a large pan combine first 6 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes until potatoes are barely soft.
Add asparagus.
Slice asparagus as it slides from can.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Blend cheese and cream.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Do not boil!

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Wash lemons; slice thin.
Place in a stainless or enamel container.
Add sugar.
Pound with wooden spoon or mallet to squeeze juice form lemon rings; stir to make syrup.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add ice water and 10 to 12 ice cubes; stir well.
Serve within 6 hours for best flavor.

title: eagle brand lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk and ReaLemon.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with whipping cream.

title: spicy hot bean dip
directions: In a food processor, mix beans, pepper and onion.
Place in a serving dish and top with salsa.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Blend together like pie crust.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: my mother-in-law's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon, onion and pepper together.
Add tomato soup, tomato sauce and creamed corn.
Mix altogether with cooked macaroni.
Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and serve.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make in balls similar to shape of buckeye.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Take balls out and put a toothpick in each ball.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Brown rice in a saucepan with butter.
When browned thoroughly, add soup and mushrooms with juice.
Simmer, covered, until done, about 45 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain syrup from 2 cans of peaches.
Combine syrup from other 2 cans with vinegar, brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add peaches.
Refrigerate.
Make at least 1 week in advance.
Great for Thanksgiving.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all
ingredients, except oil.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons into 1/8-inch
hot oil.
Flatten patties to 1/4-inch. Fry until golden brown and turn over.

title: apple crisp
directions: In 8-inch square dish arrange apple slices in layer, packing firmly (use more apples if necessary).
Combine water, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla; pour over apples.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and butter; sprinkle over apples and top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Make syrup of sugar and vinegar.
Pour hot syrup over pickles.
Cool, put in containers and put in freezer.

title: huervos rancheros
directions: Brown pork chops and jalapeno in olive oil. When brown, add Habanero peppers and 1 gallon water. When hot, add chicken soup base.
Cook until pork is tender. Check taste. Add more chicken base if needed.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oil, oleo and marshmallows together.
Add 3 quarts popcorn and peanuts if desired.
Pour in greased Bundt pan and pat down
real
good.
Turn upside down on plate and cake will eventually fall out.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Mix all ingredients together, adding boiling water last.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Boil for 2 minutes or until soft ball forms.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff and nuts.
Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 1/2 sticks oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Mix rest of oleo, eggs and sugar together; beat 5 minutes (important).
Spread over crust. Place drained pineapple on next; slice bananas on top next.
Spoon whipped topping on bananas and spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts on top and place 1/2 cherry on each serving piece.
Chill 5 hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper beans and 1/2 can onion rings. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir. Sprinkle remaining onion rings over bean mixture. Bake 5 minutes until brown. Serves 6.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir flour and frosting mix into creamed mixture by hand.
Add the nuts and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 2 hours before removing cake from pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with favorite fruit.

title: kids party punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients. Pour into punch bowl. Float rainbow sherbet and serve.

title: sweet potatoes or yams
directions: Cook either potatoes or yams with skin on until soft or a fork can pierce through it.
Cool, then peel and slice to desired thickness.
Mix bread crumbs and sugar and coat each side of the potato or yams with mixture. Fry in butter or margarine until brown on both sides.
Serve with turkey, chicken or ham dinner.

title: mushroom bake
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter 5 minutes, add mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Layer half each of bread cubes, cheeses and vegetables in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; stir well.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven, let stand five minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Put all vegetables into a large container with a lid that seals.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, water and paprika; mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour liquid over vegetables.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian lemon chicken(serves 4)
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken breasts.
Pound thin with meat hammer.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning into a large dish.
Coat chicken by dipping into flour mixture, both sides.

title: my man cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars and add eggs.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture; add oats, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Makes very thick dough.
Roll in balls and press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all in 2-quart saucepan. Stir. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cool, then refrigerate, covered, several hours. Heat slowly before serving. Strain to remove spices. Makes 8 servings.

title: cereal treats
directions: You will also need wax paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, fold in sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add the rest and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: honey peanut butter bars
directions: Place Rice Krispies in a glass baking dish.
Heat at 350° for 5 minutes.
Pour into a large greased bowl; add nuts.
Melt butter and marshmallows in saucepan.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and honey.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chocolate chips.
Place in 350° oven for 2 to 3 minutes; remove and spread melted chips.
Chill and cut.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese in a mixing bowl until creamy.
Stir in salsa, chilies and onion; mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours. Spread on flour tortilla shells.
Sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Roll and chill 24 hours.
Slice in 1/2-inch pieces and serve with salsa.

title: alma's raisin pie(december 23, 1930)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding the egg yolks.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; add raisins and nuts.
Beat well, then add egg whites.
Bake slow in a 9-inch raw pie crust.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop ham, broccoli, onion and parsley with food chopper.
Coarsely grate cheese (1 1/2 cups). Mix all ingredients except crescent rolls and set aside.
On a 13-inch baking stone, arrange crescent triangles in a circle with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside.
There should be a circle of about 3 inches in diameter in the center. Spoon filling over bases evenly.
Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under bases at the center.
Filling will not be completely covered.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dill broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients cold.
Cover over all the raw broccoli; stir often.
Marinate 24 hours.

title: seashell salad with louis dressing
directions: Cook shells to desired doneness as directed on package.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni shells, scallops, crab, shrimp, celery, olives, radishes and peppers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: panocha
directions: Butter sides of a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugars, cream, milk and butter.
Over medium heat, stir constantly until sugars dissolve and mixture boils.
Cook to a soft ball stage (238°), stirring only if necessary.
Immediately remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°), without stirring.
Add vanilla.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add eggs flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown rice-vegetable saute
directions: Heat margarine in a large skillet. When melted, add carrots and onions. Saute. Add rice. Cook over low heat 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add water, sherry, bouillon and pepper. Cover. Simmer 45 minutes to absorb liquid.
Transfer to a bowl. Set aside and keep warm.

title: aunt mary's wedding pilaf tatorian(bulghur wheat)
directions: Saute peppers and onion in oil.
Add bulghur and coat each grain.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add broth and parsley.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir once only or it will clump.

title: banana-carrot tea bread
directions: Beat the eggs well in a large bowl;
add the banana, sugar and oil; beat again.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Fold into the banana mixture.
Stir in the carrots and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch pan. Bake at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before slicing.
Freezes well.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in except the cherries.
Add flour until mixture is cake like.
Add amount of cherries you desire.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, cocoa and egg.
Add applesauce, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Blend well.
Add flour, salt and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.	Beat in buttermilk.
Add cereal and raisins.
Fill muffin pans to make desired number of muffins. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
Batter can be stored in refrigerator for up 6 weeks.

title: bride's punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, prepared as indicated; chill to slush. Add ginger ale and serve. Serves 30.

title: easy pecan squares
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs and beat well.
Add baking powder, flour and salt.
Add vanilla and fold in nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and eat.

title: apple (diabetic) pie
directions: Slice apples in saucepan; add water and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Cook until apples are tender.
Drain all but 1/2 cup water.
Add Equal, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and food coloring.
Mix well.
Prick shells with a fork and pour apple mixture into shell.
Cover with remaining shell, cut slits in top and bake as directed for shells.

title: blackened fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In a shallow dish, combine onion powder, garlic salt, red pepper, basil, white pepper, thyme, black pepper and sage.
Brush both sides of fish with some of the melted margarine.
Coat both sides of fish with seasoning mixture.

title: taco salad
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese in a small bowl.
Mix in 1/2 of the dry taco seasoning.
Spread in pan.
Top with browned hamburger and taco sauce.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or overnight (overnight is best, gives it more flavor).
Top with chopped lettuce, tomato and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Onions can also be used for topping or browned with hamburger.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat as directed on package. Bake in a Bundt or angel cake pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. You can garnish with whipped cream and fresh strawberries but it is excellent plain.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Prepare Creamy Coleslaw as above, except substitute vinaigrette for dressing.
For vinaigrette, combine vinegar, sugar, water, salad oil and, if desired, hot pepper sauce in a screw-top jar. Cover and shake well.
Continue as above.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: herbed cheese
directions: Process Swiss cheese.
Add small amount of cream cheese and herbs.
Mix thoroughly, then all remaining cream cheese, sour cream, lemon juice and pressed garlic clove.
Freezes well.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat all ingredients together.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; pat into 13 x 9-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes (no longer) in 350° oven.
Melt chocolate chips or butterscotch bits with peanut butter.
Spread onto cooled base.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.
Makes 36 bars (small). Best if kept cool.

title: mimi's rice
directions: Melt butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Lightly brown pine nuts.
Add mixed cooked rices and raisins.
Mix in skillet with browned pine nuts.
Add coconut rum.
Cook all over low to medium heat, mixing together well.
Season with thyme, salt and pepper.

title: tart
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs, raisins and vanilla. Put pie dough in muffin tins and fill each with batter and sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 10 or 12 tarts.
Bake at 400°.

title: granola bars
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 300°
for 20 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Blend shortening and peanut butter.
Add brown sugar, then add egg and vanilla.
Add flour and blend.
Shape dough into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork in crisscross fashion.
Bake at 350°.
Check after 5 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand 45 minutes.
Blend with all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: judy's no fail fudge
directions: Bring to a slow boil sugar, milk and butter; boil for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add chips and fluff.
Mix until completely melted together.
Place in a greased pan.
The thickness of pieces wanted depends on size of pan used.

title: mom's-going-to-meeting-stew
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Use tight lid.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: stained glass window cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Stir in pecans and pineapple.
Shape into 2 rolls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Chill in refrigerator several hours. Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: tracy's sweet and sour pasta salad
directions: Mix pasta and vegetables.
Mix all the rest in separate bowl from pasta and vegetables.
Pour over pasta mixture; let stand in sealed bowl overnight or at least 4 hours in refrigerator.
Toss before serving.
Makes a big batch.

title: 8 can chicken casserole(great for potlucks)
directions: Combine soups and milk in a bowl until smooth.
Add chicken, mushrooms, chow mein noodles and green beans; mix well.
Pour into two 1 1/2-quart casseroles.
Bake one at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: italian chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper; drain excess fat. Boil noodles until tender; drain.
In a large pot, combine meat, noodles, spaghetti sauce, sauce jar full of water and drained kidney beans.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.
Serve hot with bread sticks.
Extra spices can be added, if desired.

title: peter pan cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter; mix well.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Sift soda and flour and add to mixture.

title: sugar plum pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding mix. Then add eggs, oil and water and mix according to directions on cake mix box. Stir in sour cream and chocolate morsels. Pour into a greased and floured (fluted) tube pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Turn out on rack to cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cook as if for mashed potatoes.
Add salt to potatoes when cooking.

title: broccoli-rice soup
directions: Heat oil in saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add onion; cover and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Add broth and next 5 ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add broccoli; cover and cook 7 minutes or until rice and broccoli are tender.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Fill 6 quart pan with sliced potatoes to 2/3 full; add diced onions and water.
Cook until tender.
Drain all water off; add salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In a 4 quart pan, put milk and butter.
Have burner on medium heat.
Let get hot.
Dice cheese; add, stirring well all the time.
When all is melted, have flour dissolved in water, then add to mixture, stirring all the time. Pour over potatoes, then sprinkle parsley flakes over.
Put in oven and brown.

title: walnut macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender in salted water; drain and run cold water through it.
Add celery, relish or pickles, onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped walnuts.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice.
Add to salad and mix lightly.
Chill. You may garnish with egg and walnut halves.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix preserves, soup mix, water and dressing.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: free cal soup
directions: Bring to boil first 6 ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add vegetables and sweetener.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples; remove stems.
Insert wooden skewers into stem end of each apple; set aside.

title: skyline chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all ingredients and cook, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Remove onion and bay leaves.
Serve on spaghetti.

title: shrimp etouffe(a-2-fay)
directions: Season peeled shrimp with Creole seasoning. Place in refrigerator for later. Melt butter in pot. Cook onions until soft. Add garlic and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in soup and cook on low for 5 minutes, stirring often, until well blended. Add shrimp, green onions and parsley. Simmer for 15 minutes. If the shrimp makes too much liquid, you can use some of the cornstarch to thicken. Serve over cooked white long grain rice. Serves 4 easily.

title: punch
directions: Put sugar and water on to boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool and add all except ginger ale.
Before ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: homemade irish creme liqueur
directions: In blender at low speed, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth. Serve over ice, if desired.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Mix stuffing mix, celery and onion with enough hot water to make it quite moist but not soggy.
Spread on steaks and roll up. Fasten with toothpicks.
Brown all over with fat.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup and 1/2 cup of water in bowl. Add to the steaks in frying pan, being sure to scrape brown drippings from bottom; simmer, covered, about 2 hours.
Baste and then turn occasionally.

title: apple pudding
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Pour in casserole.
Add applesauce.
Pour into center; do not stir! Bake at 375° 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Serve with lemon sauce or ice cream.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Break angel food cake into pieces and add to mixture.
Put in cake pan (9 x 13-inches).
Top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: bacon-chili dip
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Drain and crumble.
Beat cheese and sour cream together until smooth and fluffy.
Fold in chilies and garlic salt, then bacon.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, vegetable sticks or chips.

title: praline cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of nuts in bottom of pan.
Combine flour and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one. Stir in vanilla.
Fold in flour until combined.
Add 1 cup nuts and stir gently.
Spoon in prepared pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add pecans last.
Stir well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: old fashioned spam spread
directions: Grind Spam, eggs and onion in food processor or old fashioned grinder.
Add rest of ingredients. Should be made 24 hours ahead of time to make best.
Serve inside cut out loaf of French or sourdough bread and serve with crackers or tortilla chips.
Great hors d'oeuvres.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: In a medium saucepan cover the raisins with water and cook them over medium heat until plump.
Drain the water from raisins. Add sour cream and boil for 10 minutes on low heat and stir.
To the sour cream and raisins add the sugar, flour, egg yolks, vanilla and salt.
Cook until thick.
Add pecans and remove from heat.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Top with meringue from the whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 4 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli pizza
directions: Rub a thin layer of olive oil over a pizza crust.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, parsley, basil and oregano.
Spread broccoli over dough.
Crumble Feta cheese over broccoli.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over entire pizza.
Bake 20 minutes until hot and bubbly at 425°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate delight pie
directions: Mix together above ingredients.
Press mixture into 13x9 cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15-20 mins. or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: microwave bernaise sauce
directions: In blender, place yolks, onion, vinegar and wine.
Microwave butter on High for 1 or 2 minutes until bubbly.
Turn blender on high and gradually add butter, mixing sauce until creamy.

title: broccoli-cheese corn bread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain it well. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: burrito pie(yields 6 servings)
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, fry 1 tortilla at a time, about 30 seconds on each side, until lightly browned and blistered.
With tongs, remove tortilla to paper towels to drain.
Discard any remaining oil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In same skillet, brown ground beef, onion and garlic until all pan juices evaporate and meat is well browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove skillet from heat; stir in green chilies, refried beans and taco sauce.
In 9-inch pie plate, place 1 tortilla; top with one-fourth of bean mixture and one-fourth of cheese.
Continue layering remaining tortillas with bean mixture and cheese.
Bake pie 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with sliced lettuce, tomato and olives.

title: fried okra and tomatoes
directions: Wash okra thoroughly.
Cut okra up into small pieces, approximately 1/2-inch pieces.
Fry 5 strips of bacon as seasoning for next step.
Fry in 3 cups of vegetable oil until somewhat crispy, approximately 35 minutes.
Squeeze oil off.
Pour in tomato sauce and whole tomatoes.
Add seasoning and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Tastes great by itself or over rice.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Add water until stiff.
Roll out on a floured surface.
