Use unbaked or bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden. Can mix up more than one at a time and freeze the dough in balls.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In a bowl, mix oil and water and add to flour mixture with a fork; press into pie plates.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 325° to 350° until golden.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add the sugar, salt and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 6 to 8 minutes). Pinch off about 2 tablespoons dough for each pretzel.
Shape as desired and place on greased baking sheets.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: quiche new mexico styleroswell, new mexico
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Serve with fruits of choice as a dip.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.

title: marinated chicken overnight
directions: Combine all ingredients, except dry mix and margarine.
Add chicken and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll chicken in dry mix and place in bottom of long casserole dish.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: drop pineapple and spice cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix Crisco, sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and egg until creamy.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown in skillet, drain fat, add 2 jars hot salsa sauce.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips (can be frozen).

title: kentucky hot brown
directions: Add flour to melted butter.
Cook until it cooks all over. Add milk, stirring to mix and while cooking, add salt, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and cheese.
Cook and stir until smooth.

title: sesame sticks
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour, cayenne, salt and oregano.
Mix until butter is completely blended into the flour mixture.
Blend in the egg and work dough with hands, or process until mixture looks like cookie dough.
Blend in Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a large bowl, combine the pumpkin, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, and evaporated milk.
Mix well. Pour into an ungreased 9 X 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over the batter in the pan.
Drizzle melted butter evenly over the top then sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for about 1 1/4 hours or until the top is set and the bottom has the texture of pumpkin pie.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: sunshine sizzle punch
directions: Empty lemonade drink mix into a large punch bowl. Add club soda and limeade concentrate. Stir until completely dissolved. Spoon raspberry sherbet into punch just before serving. Makes 18 servings, 1 cup each.

title: fresh fruit
directions: Peel and cut fruit in bite-sized wedges.
Add pineapple. Sprinkle sugar over.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Other fruit is optional.

title: bread crumb topping for vegetables
directions: In medium skillet, heat olive oil. Add onion and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes or until tender.
Add bread crumbs. Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over hot cooked vegetables.
Yields 1 cup.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix 1 cup sugar, the shortening, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt until smooth. Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Mix 1 teaspoon sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan; cool bread completely before slicing.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Add spices to pudding mix.
Add milk and stir.
Stir in pumpkin.
(As an alternative, place ingredients in 1/2 gallon jar or Tupperware sealed container and shake vigorously for 2 minutes.)
Pour into 4 to 6 small bowls.
May serve immediately or chill first in refrigerator.

title: skillet cake
directions: Melt butter and add to sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt and flavoring and mix well.
Pour into 8-inch iron skillet which has been lined with aluminum foil. Leave excess foil on either side for later use.
Cover top with almonds and sprinkle with sugar. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cake from pan with foil and when cool, wrap tightly in the foil to store.
Cut into thin strips or wedges.

title: viki's ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour, oats, brown sugar and nuts.
Spread in a thin layer on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool and crumble.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture in a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour 1/2 of the caramel topping on crumbs.
Slice and place soft ice cream on top.
Pour remaining caramel over ice cream.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Keep frozen until served.

title: oven stew
directions: Place ingredients in roaster.
Cover.
Bake for 4 hours in 275° oven.
Needs no stirring.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and vanilla and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press 1/2 marshmallow, cut side down, on each cookie.
Bake 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
Top with cocoa frosting and nuts.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Add gelatin and dissolve. Stir in applesauce.
Pour half of this mixture in 8 x 8-inch glass dish and place in refrigerator to chill.
Leave other half at room temperature.

title: grandma's christmas cookies
directions: Cream egg, sugar, butter and vanilla until fine.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Chill.
Then roll out on floured board adding more flour until dough rolls out easily.
Cut with Christmas cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost and decorate.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: date roll
directions: Mix
with
hands,
until sticks together.
Makes 2 logs. Roll in some of crumbs.
Wrap and keep in refrigerator.

title: beef goulash with noodles
directions: Heat oil in deep saucepan.
Add
beef cubes and onions. Sprinkle with flour and cook
until
lightly
brown.
Stir	in paprika and cook 3 minutes.
Add
tomato
puree,
water, salt, sugar, pepper and bay leaf; cover and
simmer
1 hour or until meat is tender.
Toss hot cooked noodles with butter and serve with goulash.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix candy and apples until well blended.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Garnish with apple slices and additional chopped Snickers.
Salad is best made and served the same day.

title: spice snaps
directions: Mix sugar and shortening. Add egg and molasses. Then blend in dry ingredients. Dough will be stiff. Take size of a walnut, roll into a ball. Roll in granulated sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except potatoes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer potatoes and sauce until all is used up.
Top with crushed corn flakes or add additional shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: green bean salad
directions: Marinate beans and chopped onions in dressing overnight. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl and mix well. Refrigerate.
The next day, drain green beans and combine with the sour cream sauce.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (add blueberries last).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Use Bundt pan or muffin tins.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Have oven heating to 350° (325° for glass dish). In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly (also easily done in food processor). Press firmly into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Then combine all ingredients, including sauteed onion.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until bubbles.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: mom's sunday beef
directions: Sear roast.
(Place meat on hot frypan and quickly turn as meat browns immediately.)
Place roast on rack in roasting pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Roast in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes per pound until center of roast is 160°.
Serve with potatoes, peas and homemade gravy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter. Add soups and broth. Put rice and part of soup mix in 9 x 13 pan. Add chicken. Pour rest of mix over top. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 3 hours.

title: treasure cay spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Crumble beef in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave 5 minutes on Full power.
Drain fat.
Mix in sauce, macaroni and water. Microwave, covered, for 13 minutes on High, stirring once. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Fry crumbled meat and drain.
Saute vegetables in oil until tender-crisp.
Add soup, tomatoes and beef.
Mix well and season as desired.
Layer in casserole dish with chips, topping with crushed chips and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no fat dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in cool dry place.
Excellent hot drink.

title: spiced beets
directions: Combine beets and onions.
Mix water, salt, vinegar, sugar, cloves and cinnamon together in a saucepan.
Simmer for 10 minutes; add beets and onions and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in skin in salty water until tender.
Drain and peel and take out core; mash.
Add egg, butter, Worcestershire sauce, cheese, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish and cover with crushed crackers.
Dot with butter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and then
blend in 2-3 cups Cool Whip.

title: rice stuffing
directions: Crumble sausage and hamburger.
Add chopped onion, celery, salt, sage and parsley.
Saute in large skillet or roaster until all are well cooked.
Add rice, mushrooms and chicken broth.
Add enough water to steam rice until well done.
Cook on low heat; stir occasionally and add more poultry seasoning to your taste. This will serve 12 to 15.

title: mixed greens(weight watchers)
directions: Remove any tough stems from greens; wash and drain to thoroughly remove sand and chop coarsely.
In Dutch oven over medium heat, heat oil; add onion and celery and cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in greens; cover and cook 10 minutes until greens are wilted, stirring occasionally. Add bacon, vinegar, red pepper flakes and salt; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups water; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours, adding more water if necessary.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except rolls.
Divide rolls into 4 sets of 2 rolls each.
Press seams together of 2 rolls to form a square.
Spoon 1/4 of chicken mixture onto the middle of the square.
Fold corners up to make the "hut".
Place seam side down on foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake according to crescent roll package directions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add cinnamon and rum flavoring and beat well into sweet potatoes.
Add the orange juice, pecans and raisins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover top completely with the marshmallows and allow them to melt slightly before serving.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and onion.
Put in pot and let cook a little before adding all other ingredients.
Add tomato soup last, after everything else has cooked for a while.
Do not have to cook very long.
As soon as potatoes and onion are done, you only have to cook just to thicken.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini.
Boil until tender and drain.
Pour into pan and mash slightly.
Add butter to hot zucchini. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix.
Put in buttered dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Fry sausages; drain.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine milk, eggs, flour, butter and salt in a blender.
Process one minute or until smooth.
Pour over sausages.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until topping is puffed and golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, milk, vanilla and butter. Add cocoa and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, add the beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and then add to the butter mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Form into long rolls about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Slice the cookies to the desired thickness and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10-15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and let set overnight before serving!

title: candy mounds
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight. Cut in squares.
Dip in chocolate melted with paraffin. Store in refrigerator.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook according to directions on grits box 1 cup grits.

When grits are thick, add garlic cheese, cut into small pieces and 1 stick oleo. Break into a 1 cup measuring cup the 2 eggs; beat with fork. Add milk to fill cup. Add this to grits; mix well. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Let set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain well.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, mushrooms, water, rice, salt and pepper.
Add sausage and onion.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake until all liquid is absorbed (approximately 5 to 10 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana-wheat quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch pan.
In a large bowl, blend all ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: cheese kugel
directions: Cook noodles according to instructions on package.
Beat together eggs, cream cheese, 6 tablespoons sugar, butter, cottage cheese and milk.
Add cinnamon.
Mix cooked noodles into the mixture and toss well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: grits
directions: Put eggs in a measuring cup and finish filling cup with milk. Salt.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix corn, onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and cucumber.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Just before serving, add tomatoes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and egg.
Pour mixture over apples.
Add butter and cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange punch
directions: Empty juice and syrup into bowl.
Mix. Add sherbet and ice. Pour ginger ale over this. Add orange soda. Stir.
Allow most of the ice to melt prior to serving.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Cut ends off zucchini, but do not pare.
Cook in boiling water for 5 to 7 minutes; drain.
Cut in half lengthwise.
With tip of spoon, carefully scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Dice scooped out squash; drain excess liquid.
Sprinkle squash (diced) and shells with salt.
Combine eggs, corn, green onion, seasoned salt and diced squash.
Spoon lightly into zucchini shells.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over tops.
Bake 4 or 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: easy spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cornmeal and melted butter in a bowl, adding boiling water slowly.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour into hot 8-inch square baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in your blender and blend until well mixed. Store in the refrigerator.
Serve on your tossed salads.

title: angel pie(this is a heavenly pie.)
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add cream of tartar and sugar; beat until mixture is stiff and glossy.
Pour into a pie plate and bake in a 275° oven for 20 minutes, then in a 300° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix the baking soda in the buttermilk until it fizzes.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add water last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh okra salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Let cool.
Then crumble.
Chop pepper, onion and tomato.
Fry okra the way you prefer; drain.
Mix okra, bacon, pepper, onion and tomato in bowl and serve while warm.

title: a successful christian
directions: For 2 cups of love add 1 pint of faith with gentleness; separate peace from strife and add 1 cup of peace to faith and the love mixture.

title: chilled vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, cider vinegar and oil to boil over medium heat. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring often, then cool for 30 minutes and set aside. Finely chop green pepper, onion and celery. Add pimento, drained peas, green beans and Shoepeg corn. Add salt and pepper.
Pour cooled ingredients over vegetable mixture. Mix well. Chill 8 hours before serving.

title: mini fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs, honey and vanilla until fluffy.
In small bowl, stir flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg together.
Blend the flour mixture, half at a time, into the batter mixture.
Stir in the raisins, fruit and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 60 cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/2 stick oleo and nuts.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.
It's best if you allow it to set a little while before serving.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, egg, oats and soup mix together until well blended. Form balls and brown in skillet.
Pour off excess grease and drain meatballs.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Line greased pan with Crisco and brown paper bag or wax paper.

title: molly's favorite hot dip
directions: Scoop out bread and cut or tear pieces to use as dippers. Mix all other ingredients and pour into bread bowl. Bake at 350° until dip is warm and cheese is melted. Serve with Frito scoops, crackers, celery or other vegetables and bread pieces.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add water, vanilla, flour, salt, baking soda and egg yolks.
Mix and put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites until stiff; stir in 1 cup brown sugar. Spread over batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cover with foil if top darkens while baking.

title: coconut-chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in eggs, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and coconut.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until set.

title: piquant fish
directions: Place fish in cold water and lemon juice for a few minutes. Place fish in a baking dish.
Pour sauce (recipe to follow) over fish coating very well.
Bake at 500° for 10
minutes or until flaky.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup of topping, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix until well blended and spread over cooled crust.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Combine sour cream and Italian dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Add beans, tomato and onion.
Mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve in lettuce cup if desired.
Makes about 2 servings.
Can be doubled or multiplied to any amount you need.
Leftovers keep well in the refrigerator.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire cooling rack.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen cookies. Calories: 74 calories per cookie.

title: carnation whipping instructions
directions: Chill evaporated milk in refrigerator tray until ice crystals form around edges of ice tray (15 to 20 minutes).
Pour into a bowl.
Whip until stiff (about 1 minute).
Add lemon juice.
Whip very stiff (2 minutes).

title: homemade cocoa
directions: Thoroughly sift all ingredients together.
The more you sift it, the better it is.
Add 4 to 5 teaspoons as desired with water. Use with hot water only.

title: easy chocolate truffles
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add melted chocolate chips and vanilla; mix well.
Refrigerate approximately 1 hour.

title: hot fudge delight
directions: Pour milk in bowl, add pudding and mix with mixer; place in refrigerator.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
When pudding has set, add Cool Whip.
Pour half over graham crackers and then cover with graham crackers again.
Now pour the rest of pudding mixture and add more graham crackers.
Follow directions on hot fudge for microwave and pour over top graham crackers.
Place in refrigerator until needed.
You can also use any fruit topping.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Then add sour cream.
In a small bowl, mix 1/4 cup sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Spread 1/2 batter mixture.
Top with 1/2 crumb mixture.
Spread other 1/2 of batter.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Sift together flour and salt; add with oats to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape to form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten, using a fork.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken provencale
directions: Skin chicken.
Sprinkle salt over chicken (set aside).
Heat oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook 5 minutes on each side or until browned.
Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Cook macaroni with salt in 3 quarts of water.
Drain, when done, and combine all ingredients.
Put into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cube and cook potatoes; drain.
Cube Velveeta cheese.
Combine potatoes, cheese, onion, mayonnaise and salt in casserole baking dish.
Spread evenly in dish.
Top with olives and bacon, alternating in rows.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger skillet
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Return to skillet.
Add brown gravy mix, soy sauce, onion soup mix and carrots.
Add equal amounts of rice and water.
Cover and cook until rice is tender. Sauce should be thickened.
Great dish for in a hurry!

title: citrus filled dutch pancake
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until foamy.
Stir in milk, flour and salt. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in oven.
Pour batter in round cake pan. Bake in oven 20 minutes at 425°.
Squeeze 1 orange for juice.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Boil 6 minutes on stove.
Add orange sections.
Pour over top of pancake.
Enjoy.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat one cup of the drained pear juice to boiling, add the jello, stirring until it is dissolved.
Stir in the softened cream cheese,
Kool Whip and pears which have been mashed.
Mix well.
Stir in the walnuts.
Refrigerate until gelled.

title: skillet chicken and broccoli
directions: Put pasta on to boil, using package directions.
While it is boiling, place broccoli and onion in water in a large skillet.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients, dry.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of dry mix to 1 cup of hot water.
Store remaining dry tea in an airtight container.

title: trail mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugars, peanut butter, butter, shortening, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed or mix with wooden spoon.
Stir in flour, oats, baking powder and baking soda thoroughly.
Stir in M&M's, peanuts and raisins.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, plus nuts.
Mix sugar, oil, zucchini and beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture; blend well.
Divide batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan at once and cool.
Good to wrap in aluminum foil and freeze.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix Part 1 together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Bake first 1/2 hour without sauce.)

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients. Add buttermilk last. Bake in unbaked shell 35 minutes at 375°.

title: key lime chicken broil
directions: Wash chickens; pat dry.
Place skin side down on rack in broiler pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Brush generously over chickens.
Broil, turning every 10 minutes and brushing with more lime mixture, 40 minutes or until the chickens are tender and richly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in the flour, salt and cinnamon. Drop 1 teaspoon of dough onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling on top of dough, then cover with another 1/2 teaspoon of dough.

title: jug pickles
directions: Boil 1/2 gallon water and 1 cup pickling salt.	Pour over cucumbers in jug.
Pack cucumbers down well in jug.
Let set for 7 days.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: In a greased casserole, mix chopped cooked chicken and cooked wild rice.
Add green pepper, mushrooms, mushroom soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: date nut bread
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in large bowl, then pour 2 1/4 cups boiling water over and let stand 15 minutes while mixing the remaining ingredients.
Mix with first mixture.
Have 3 (3 x 9 x 5-inch) loaf pans ready, greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Peel off waxed paper at once.
Let cool, then store in freezer.
Best made 2 months before use. Avoid holiday rush!

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, oleo and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Wash carrots; scrape and cut in half diagonally.
Parboil carrots for 15 minutes.
Place carrots in a buttered casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat until cornstarch is dissolved and sauce is slightly thickened.
Pour over carrots and dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes; uncover and bake a few minutes longer until some of the liquid has evaporated. Serves 6.

title: cole slaw salad
directions: Beat eggs; add vinegar and sugar.
Place over medium heat. Stir until thickened.
Add hot to shredded cabbage.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts; place them in bottom of baking dish. Shred into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese and spread on top of artichokes.
Place in
oven at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: sod suppesweet soup
directions: In large sauce pan place prunes, raisins, orange slices, lemon slices, tapioca, sugar and cinnamon stick.
Add water to cover fruit; stir to combine.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Before cooking add diced apple and 1 c. more water.
Place over moderate heat (250°); bring to a boil.
Simmer; stirring occationally until apples are tender (about 20-25 minutes).
Note:
Soup should be thick.
May be served hot or cold, but is traditionally served hot on Christmas.
Makes about 3 quarts.
P.S.
Cook sago over boiling water 1 hour before adding to rest as it takes longer to soften.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand for 15 minutes.
Form into balls the size of a walnut or patties.
Fry until brown. Best if served immediately, but are fine reheated later.
Can be put in a dish with gravy and reheated if desired.
(I usually double the amount, they are so good!)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and cream to ingredients and chill.

title: yvonne's pepperoni loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With a rolling pin, roll pizza dough into a large square (make sure you don't roll dough too thin).
Add cold cuts and green pepper strips one layer at a time on top of dough, covering dough entirely.
Without losing any of the cold cuts, start to roll the dough.
Once closed, dampen the top with water.
Pinch the sides closed and lightly dampen them.
Bake for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool for 10 minutes. cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: stuffed peppers(serves 4)
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine beef, 1 tablespoon green onions, garlic and pepper.
Cut green peppers in half; scoop out seed and fill with veal mixture.
Place green peppers in a preheated skillet, meat side down.
Brown meat, then turn peppers over; dissolve tomato soup in water.
Add remaining green onions and pour over peppers.
Cover and cook for 1/2 hour medium heat. Remove green peppers.
Place bean sprouts in soup mixture and cook for 5 minutes.

title: nontoxic finger paint
directions: Mix 1/4 cup cold water in gelatin.
In another pan, mix 3/4 cup cold water with cornstarch in pan and stir.
Add boiling water and stir in diluted gelatin.
Color with fruit drink powder or fruit juice.
Cool in refrigerator before using.
Store in plastic jars.

title: sweet georgia peach pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; fill with peaches.
Beat eggs well in bowl; add sugar, flour and shortening.
Pour over peaches.
It will form its own top crust in baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 325°, cook 40 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature. Slice and serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: brattens boston clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams.
Pour over vegetables.
Add enough water to cover; simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, Eagle Brand milk and evaporated milk. Soak gelatine in cool water, then heat to melt.
Add to other mixture when cool.
Add vanilla.
Put in freezer container and fill to 2/3 full with whole milk.

title: bean soup
directions: In a heavy kettle, soak beans overnight.
Drain beans.
Cover with 2 quarts water.
Scrub and score ham hocks.
Add to kettle. Cut up or dice all vegetables; add all at once.
Add rice. Season to taste.
Cook until beans are done; stir often.
Add more water as needed.
Remove ham hocks; cut apart.
Add any ham to soup.

title: kathy's easy rolls
directions: Combine in bowl
and mix with spoon.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Grease muffin pan.
Place heaping spoonfuls in cups. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: The ingredients in this recipe are approximate.
I add according to taste.

title: georgia's zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rev.  c. s. bland's hopping beans and rice
directions: Cook rice until done; melt butter or margarine in saucepan. Add chopped pepper and onions.
Saute until tender and season to taste.
Heat pork and beans.
Place rice in serving dish; layer with pork and beans.
Pour sauteed vegetables over top.
Garnish with parsley.
Chopped mushrooms or bacon bits, optional.
Best served with steak or chicken.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Brown pork until crumbly and well done, about 20 minutes.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Drain fat.
Add salsa and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Beat together milk, eggs and flour, then add cheese.
Layer chiles, pork mixture and cheese mixture in greased 8-inch pan, ending with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oh so good cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail with juice.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cherry supreme angel food
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sour cream until thick, then fold in the pie filling.
Spoon over cake.

title: succotash
directions: Saute the onion and corn in a saucepan with a little butter or bacon fat.
Add the tomatoes and the okra; cover with water.
Add salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar.
Let simmer an hour.

title: date nut pinwheels
directions: Filling:
Cook dates, sugar, water and butter until thick. Add nuts.

title: squash cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except 1 cup of flour and chocolate chips).
Grease and flour an 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add flour with chocolate chips to mixture and blend in by hand.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Into a greased baking dish or casserole, place a layer of tomatoes.
Add half the cucumber and onion slices and half the bread crumbs.
Repeat with more tomatoes and remaining cucumbers, onions and crumbs.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese. Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 40 minutes.

title: scallops exceptional
directions: Saute broccoli, peppers, garlic and basil in margarine.
Add scallops; continue cooking for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in Velveeta cheese and sherry; continue heating until cheese is melted.
Serve over rice.
(Also works well with shrimp.)

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Then mix oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight to marinate.

title: shrimp and scallop scampi
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place cleaned, deveined shrimp and scallops in a shallow baking dish or pan.
Squeeze the lemon, add olive oil, butter and minced garlic and pour over shrimp and scallops.
Place under broiler for 2 to 4 minutes on one side, then turn and place under broiler another 2 to 4 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle paprika and pepper to taste.
Garnish with parsley.
Cook pasta al dente.
Pour the shrimp and scallops over with all pan juices. Make more juice if you would like and our over cooked linguine or angel hair pasta.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll dough balls in 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar mixture.
Drop into greased and floured tube pan.
Boil remaining ingredients and pour over cake, then bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hummus(great as a dip for fresh vegetables.)
directions: Drain garbanzo beans.
In blender mix with lemon juice, garlic and tahini.
Blend until smooth.
It may be necessary to add up to 1/4 cup water to make mixture smooth.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, and boil for 30 minutes. Add butter when cooked.
Let cool before icing cake.

title: dill pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with salt water; let stand 24 hours.
Drain well.
Bring to a boil the vinegar water, pickle spice and dill seed.
Add small whole cucumbers to mixture; just dip in and right back out.
Put cucumbers in quart jars.
Add 2 garlic cubes, 2 hot peppers (if you want hot pickles) and 1 teaspoon dill seed in each jar.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Melt the oleo. Add the other ingredients, stirring over low heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a full rolling boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and beat until creamy.

title: *zucchini rounds
directions: Mix biscuit mix, cheese and pepper.
Stir in eggs and beat until moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
Fry in 2 tablespoons butter, about 3 minutes on each side.
Makes about 12 cakes or 6 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, mix the sugar, oleo and eggs until well blended. Sift flour, soda and salt into same bowl, alternating with coffee-cocoa mixture.
Add vanilla and mix all.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers or 1 rectangle.

title: almond chicken
directions: Mix egg white, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons oil, soy sauce, cornstarch and wine.
Place diced chicken in this mixture and marinate for 1 hour.
Heat 5 tablespoons cooking oil to hot and stir-fry almonds for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and place on plate.

title: super simple vegetable soup
directions: Mix browned and drained ground beef and garlic salt with V-8 juice and mixed vegetables.
Cook in crock-pot 4 to 6 hours on high.

title: waldorf salad cake
directions: Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan, about 9 x 3 1/2-inches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put 1 cup of the seasoned croutons in a 2-quart casserole. Brown ground chuck and onion and spread over croutons.
Cook broccoli; drain off water and add to casserole.
Add remaining croutons.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Top with onion rings. Heat through in a 300° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and egg yolks until smooth.
Add hot water. Combine dry ingredients and sift into sugar mixture.
Stir in pecans, potatoes and vanilla, continuing to blend.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in a greased, shallow pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: picadillo dip
directions: Mix meats together by hand, put into a large pan and barely cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir meat until well blended.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot in a chafing dish with chips.
Freezes well.
It disappears so quickly that you need to double recipe.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Leave in refrigerator overnight before icing cake.

title: sugar-free easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and water; add pineapple juice.
If desired, pour some in a round pan and freeze for an ice ring.
Chill remaining punch.
Pour over ice ring just before serving.
Add 7-Up last. Makes fifty 1/2-cup servings.

title: turkey chili
directions: Cook onions, garlic and pepper in oil.
Add turkey and cook until it loses its color.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, slowly, stirring often.
Good with corn bread.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust

title: corn creole
directions: Chop pepper and onion and saute in bacon drippings; add meat; brown. Stir in corn, milk, corn meal, and seasoning. Pour into greased 2 qt. casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs on top. Dot with butter and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pickled peppers
directions: Pierce jalapeno chili peppers with knife tip.
Combine remaining ingredients in large jar or glass bowl.
Let peppers soak in solution overnight.
(Weight down so peppers are below liquid.)
Drain liquid in saucepan.
Bring to boil and add peppers.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: cranberry-pear pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with half of the pastry.
Place the cranberries in a saucepan with a little water.
Cover and cook for 6 to 8 minutes until the skins pop. Add the tapioca, sugar, salt and pears.
Mix well and cool.
Turn into the prepared pie plate and dot with butter.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop onto cookie sheet; flatten slightly and add raisins on top.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic together.
Stir in the soup and then add the other ingredients.
Let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring every now and then.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: punjabi chana(spicy garbanzo beans)
directions: Drain and rinse garbanzo beans.
Set aside.
Heal oil in skillet over medium flame.
When hot, add cumin and black mustard seed.
When the mustard has stopped popping, add the onion, chili and garlic.
Saute until the onion is clear.
Add to the saute, the garbanzo beans.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add tomato, salt, turmeric and Chana Masala*.
Toss seasonings with beans.
Add enough water to make a gravy (about 1/2 cup).
Cook until liquid becomes a nice spicy gravy, 5 minutes or so.
Before serving, top with butter and lemon juice.
Serve immediately with rice or chapati.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine salad dressing and pickle juice.
Add to macaroni; add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Serve surrounded with lettuce.
Garnish with hard-cooked eggs, tomato wedges and green pepper slices.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Heat butter or margarine in 4 cup glass measure at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Stir until smooth.
Cook at High power for 3 1/4 to 4 1/2 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Stir 3 times.
Add cheese and stir until completely melted.

title: chutney
directions: Peel and cut fruit; add 1-quart vinegar.
Boil for 20 minutes. Combine sugar and second quart of vinegar; boil until it is a thick syrup.
Pour off most of the liquid from the fruit and add to the syrup.
Boil this until it is thick.
Combine this thick syrup with the rest of the ingredients and fruit, except the ginger; cook 30 minutes.
Add chopped ginger and its syrup and cook 10 minutes longer.
Bottle the chutney.
Flavor improved if placed in sun for several days.
Yields 4 to 5 pints.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, add salt and pepper.
Lightly grease a 10 x 15-inch baking dish and line with 1/2 of tortillas (break up for easier serving).
Cover with 1/2 the meat, sprinkle with 1/2 the potatoes, peas, olives, onion and cheese.
Repeat, except for cheese.

title: baked bean stew
directions: Save drained juices for adding to leftover beans for reheating.

title: apple crisp for two
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apples in 9 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle water, lemon juice and cinnamon on top.
Mix remaining until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples and bake about 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: double delight cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix per package instructions in 13 x 9 pan.
Cool completely.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger, onion and salt and pepper. Blend tomato paste, Ranch Style beans and sugar and mix with hamburger mixture. Layer casserole dish with Doritos and hamburger mixture. Top with Cheddar or American cheese and crunched Doritos.

title: plain pastry
directions: Good for fried apple pies.
Two recipes makes 16 pies.
I mix it up and let stay in refrigerator overnight.

title: almond rice pudding
directions: In large saucepot warm milk with salt.
Add rice; stir constantly, approximately 50 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk and raisins.
Stir until bubbly and the rice is no longer "spiny." In the meantime mix the remainder of evaporated milk, eggs, sugar and almond extract in a bowl, take 1 cup of rice and mix into egg mixture.
Add mixture to rice.
Cook again until bubbly.
Let cool; add 1 more cup of whole milk.
Refrigerate overnight, stir and add more milk to desired consistency.

title: bran nut muffins(microwave)
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, bran and nuts.

title: pat-a-pizza
directions: Brown ground beef over low heat.
Pat biscuits into 4-inch circles on a baking sheet.
Put 1 tablespoon tomato sauce on each 4-inch circle, then bake at 400° for 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Pour off grease from browned ground beef and then add salt and oregano to the meat.
Put some meat, then cheese on each pizza.
Turn oven down to 325° and heat pizza in oven until cheese is melted.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Let cake rest in pan 5 minutes before turning out.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells. Refrigerate, slice and eat.

title: exquisite pie
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Fold in coconut, pecans and raisins.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: sinful shrimp pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
While this is cooking, melt margarine in a skillet and saute the sliced green onions, garlic and mushrooms.
When these are done (4 to 8 minutes), add shrimp.
If fresh, cook for another 4 minutes.
If canned, just heat through.
Add olive oil and salt and pepper. Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old-time cinnamon jumbles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Chill the dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop by rounded teaspoons, 2-inches apart, on lightly greased sheet.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until set, but not brown. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: skillet beef supreme
directions: Brown meat in hot
Wesson
in
large heavy skillet. Add next 4 ingredients and cook
to
minutes.
(You want the vegetables to be crisp.) Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, liquid and seasonings.
Add
to
skillet, stirring to mix thoroughly. Add mushrooms.
Stir, cooking
until liquid is clear and shiny and beans are
tender.
Garnish
with
pimientos.
Serve
with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Meat Sauce:
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add cans of prepared spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, water and basil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer covered about 1 hour.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Add 1 teaspoon soda
mixed in 1/4 cup warm water.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch fried puffs
directions: Heat oil (2 to 3 inches) to 375°.
Beat milk, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup oil, the eggs, baking powder, salt, mace and 1 cup of the flour in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour and currants.

title: peanut butter goodies(no bake)
directions: Mix margarine, milk, sugar and salt in large kettle.
Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes. Take from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats; mix well. Pour on a cookie sheet or drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: pig out cake
directions: Mix cake mix with oranges with juice, oil and eggs.
Bake at 325° in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla with beater. Slice the first roll of cookie dough and place on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat or push together to form crust.
Pour mixture on top.
Spread evenly.
Slice the second roll of cookie dough and place over batter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning (do not add water as package directs).
Put beef mixture in greased 10-inch pie plate or casserole dish.
Spread chilies over meat and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together for 1 minute with mixer or 15 seconds in blender.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheddar dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze dry broccoli.
Combine all ingredients, except save 1/4 cup Cheddar to sprinkle on top.
Put in quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lazy daisy frosting
directions: Mix sugar and coconut together.
Add melted butter and cream. Mix well.
Cream may be added to make smooth.
Spread on cake (cake may be warm).
Place in 375° oven under flame at least 5 to 6 inches below flame.
Watch until a delicate brown.
Makes 8 inch layer square.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat milk over boiling water.
Beat eggs; add salt and sugar. Gradually add milk to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in pan at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
Let cool until partly thickened.
Then beat in cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry
ingredients.
Add
egg
yolks	and milk.
Cook over low
heat
until thick or double boiler.
Add vanilla and butter. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: pickled jalapenos
directions: Note:
Need 8 clean hot pint jars with lids.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken.
Put oil in 10-inch frying pan.
Heat over medium heat. Add chicken. Saute slowly about 6 minutes or until white.
Remove from pan.
Drain on paper towel.
If using frozen asparagus, cook by instructions. Drain. Place asparagus on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Place sauteed chicken over asparagus.
Mix together undiluted chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in deep cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries; reserve juice.
Heat juice on stove and dissolve jello in heated juice.
Let cool.
Add Coke. Let chill in refrigerator until thickened, but not gelled.
Stir in cherries, pecans, pineapple and cream cheese.
Make day before serving for best flavor.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: venison stew
directions: Place shoulder in crock and cover with vinegar combined with onions and bay leaves.
Marinate in mixture for 2 days.
Wash meat in cold water.
Add to boiling water and stew until tender. Remove from water and bone.
Dice carrots, celery and potatoes. Cook in meat broth until tender.
Cut meat and add to vegetables. Thicken broth; salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
Cover bottom of baked pastry shell with one-half of choicest berries.
Heat remaining berries in water until berries are soft, 4 to 5 minutes on High.

title: south carolina barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soy sauce and butter.
Simmer 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in soy sauce and butter. Serve warm or cold.

title: pineapple zucchini loaf
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts and raisins.
Add pineapple and liquid.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut balls
directions: Roast
the peanuts lightly in the oven; cool and grind. Boil the sugar with 2 cups of water until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water (240°).	Add the ground peanuts and continue
cooking, stirring constantly, until bottom of the pan can be seen in the wake of the spoon.	Remove from flame.
Add the egg
yolks, cinnamon,
salt
and vanilla and beat the mixture into
a
paste. Press
mixture
into
small balls with wooden paddles
moistened in cold water.
Arrange on wax paper lined tray and dust with powdered sugar.
Serve when dry.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; place on paper towels and press until barely moist.
Combine spinach, mayo, sour cream, onion, water chestnuts and vegetable soup mix; stir well.
Cover and chill several hours. Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 3 small greased pans. Sprinkle on top 1/2 cup white sugar, mixed with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in greased casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 stick melted margarine with cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Put egg in cup and fill with milk.
Mix with dry ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth.
Boil 15 minutes uncovered and 5 minutes covered.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bakes
directions: Boil in large pan first 4 ingredients, then add remaining 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Ready to eat.
Yields approximately 36 cookies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon with sugar.
Add shortening.
Mix to cream.
Add eggs and beat.
Add chopped apples and water.
Add flour that has been sifted and beat.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Soak bread in milk about 5 minutes, then crush with hands or stir until well mixed.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and fruit.
Pour melted margarine into bottom of thick pan then add pudding.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Scatter bacon over bottom of 13 x9 x 2-inch casserole.
Layer potatoes, onions, carrots and pork chops in skillet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine 1 cup beef broth, garlic and ginger, pour over pork chops and vegetables.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour, or until carrots are easily pierced with a fork and meat is almost tender; remove from oven.
Increase temperature to 375°.
Place uncoverd in oven and bake 12 minutes longer or until pork chops are lightly browned.
Drain off cooking liquid, reserving 1 cup.

title: spicy pretzels
directions: Mix oil, garlic, dill, lemon pepper and Ranch dressing.
Toss in pretzels (small pieces).
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Use all oil mixture.
Loose pretzel bits can be purchased at some markets.
Boxed ones can be used also.

title: washboard salad
directions: Beat margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese until fluffy. Add pineapple.
Lightly arrange layer of whole cookies in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with half the creamed mixture.
Prepare jello as per package instructions.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Whip jello until fluffy; spread on top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Bake in 10-inch pie plate (glass is best) at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cantonese peas
directions: Mix bread and butter together and spread over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper; mix well together. Put in a greased 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Top with a few pats of butter; cover.
Potatoes may be stored in the refrigerator for several days.
Before serving, bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 45 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad souffle
directions: Cut 2 slices bread.
Place in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Combine turkey, vegetables, mayonnaise, soup and seasonings; spoon over cubes.
Trim crusts from remaining bread; arrange slices on top of turkey mixture.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over all.
Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until set.
Sprinkle cheese over top during last few minutes of baking.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour 1/2 vanilla pudding over cake.
Mix strawberries with glaze; pour 1/2 of mixture over pudding.
Add 1 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate crackle top cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla extract until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Melt chocolate over hot water; add and mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts. Chill 2 to 3 hours, until stiff enough to handle.

title: cole slaw - oh so easy!
directions: Mix all but cabbage.
Slowly add grated cabbage to desired consistency.
Can be used right away but better to refrigerate for an hour or so.
Stir then serve.
You might add more cabbage to the consistency you like after removing from refrigerator.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth (at least 2 minutes with electric mixer).
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
When cool, punch hole in cake with fork.
Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar; blend eggs.
Mix and sift flour and salt.
Add chopped dates, mashed bananas and chopped walnuts.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients all together; beat well. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: filling for pies (fruit)
directions: Mix sugar and egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix that together, then add flour.
Put fruit in pie shell.
Add a little sugar on top of fruit.
Pour pie filling on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of mushroom soup, onion soup mix, beef, egg and bread crumbs.
In a 2 quart oblong baking dish, firmly shape into 8 X 4 inch loaf.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
To make the gravy, spoon off the fat, reserving 1 to 2 tablespoons of drippings.
In a 1 quart saucepan, combine remaining mushroom soup, water and drippings.
Over low heat, warm gravy thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve over meat loaf. Option:
Mushrooms can be added to the gravy. If you've got a gravy lover, add an extra can of cream of mushroom soup to the gravy mix.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 7-Up.
After well mixed, add 7-Up and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in a slice of bacon.
Mix together the sour cream and soup.
Pour over the chicken.
Line bottom of casserole dish with chipped beef, broken into pieces.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Baste at end of 2 hours.

title: beef tacos
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in medium skillet.
Drain fat. Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Arrange taco shells on baking sheet. Warm in oven for 5 to 7 minutes. Fill each of the taco shells with some of the meat mixture, tomatoes, cheese and lettuce.
Serve with taco sauce.
Makes 12 tacos.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into bite size balls. Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat Oven 350°. Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix apples, cinnamon, and sugar together. Set aside.

Mix sugar, flour, eggs, baking powder, vanilla, orange juice and oil. Beat well for 10 min. Pour 1\2 mixture into tube pan. Then put apple mixure in pan. Add remaining mixture on top. Bake for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into small balls hamburger, bread, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over medium heat until done. Drain on paper towel.

title: ground venison jerky
directions: Mix ground venison with pieces.
Roll between wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Mix liquid smoke, vinegar and water.
Brush on meat.
Bake on lowest temperature for 3 to 4 hours.
Prop oven door ajar.
When meat is dry, cut in strips and store in a tight container.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Butter glass rectangular Pyrex pan.
Pour mixed peaches with juice in pan.
Cover peaches with cake mix.
Place 1/4 stick butter, shaved, over cake mix.
Bake approximately 45 minutes. Serve with French vanilla ice cream.

title: cabbage cacciatore
directions: Brown meat in skillet with first 6 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Put cabbage on top.
Mix basil and oregano into tomato sauce.
Pour over cabbage. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve over rice.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Place sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large bowl and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to first mixture, alternately with milk and poppy seed mixture.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Invert on cake rack to cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: canneloni
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; add carrot and onion.
Saute until onion is soft.
Add garlic powder, Italian herb seasoning, veal and ground meat and saute until meat is brown.
Add white wine and simmer on low for 30 to 45 minutes.
Put the meat and vegetables a little at a time in the blender and puree.
When all meat has been pureed, add egg yolks, salt, pepper, 3 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese, parsley and 1/2 cup of the Mornay sauce; mix thoroughly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together corn, eggs, flour, sugar and milk.
Put in greased casserole. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Cook sugar, salt and evaporated milk and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Then boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Take half of water and bring to boil; stir in Jell-O. Then add rest of water. Let Jell-O mixture set in refrigerator until it starts to jell, then stir in apples, cinnamon and cranberries. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Clean and boil chicken with onion and bell pepper; take out chicken and boil spaghetti in same water chicken was boiled in. When tender, add cheese, pimentos, soup and chicken.

title: "blondie" brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Set aside.
Combine butter flavor Crisco and milk in large saucepan.
Place on low heat until butter flavor Crisco melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add egg.
Stir until well blended.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: oreo torte
directions: Crush cookies and reserve some crumbs for top of dessert.
Put remainder in 9 x 13-inch pan and drizzle melted butter over crumbs.
Cool, then spread with 1 container of whipped topping. Prepare pudding according to directions.
Blend in softened cream cheese and carefully pour over whipped topping layer.
Top with remaining container of whipped topping and sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs.
Freeze until serving time, thawing slightly before cutting into pieces.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump into 9 x 13-inch pan pineapple, coconut and yellow cake mix.
Press down, then cut into pieces the margarine and place on top and top then with chopped pecans.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake together.
Bake in 3 layer cake pans at 300° to 350° about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter and seed apples; I do not peel.
Cook, covered, preferably without water being sure they don't stick until mushy. Put through blender or food processor for thick sauce.
Add 1 cup of sugar (you can add less if you desire) for every 2 cups of sauce.
Put sugared sauce in a large, deep cooker (I use our canner) in oven at 350°.
I cook for at least 4 to 6 hours.
Cook until it is as thick as you want.
I have cooked it all day.
After it has finished cooking, add the oil of cinnamon to taste.
Just a few drops may be all you need; oil of cinnamon is potent!
Pour into hot, ready canning jars and seal.
The butter is so hot it has never been necessary to can in a canner.
The jars always seal fine.

title: pumpkin roll-ups
directions: Grease jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides), line with wax paper and grease paper.
Mix and pour the batter on top of wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake upside down on cloth tea towel dusted with 10x sugar.
Pull off paper carefully. Roll in towel.
Cool.
Unroll and fill.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine preserves and buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture.
Beat until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Wrap loaf and store overnight in cool place.
Good served with strawberry butter.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend the graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and 4 tablespoons of melted butter; place on bottom of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: basic brownies
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar, beating thoroughly.
Melt butter.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Blend. Mix in flour, salt, baking powder and chocolate.
Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Melt fat in heavy aluminum or iron pot.
Arrange a layer of beef, onion, rice and potatoes on vegetables in skillet.
Cover pan and cook slowly on top unit for 1 hour.
Can be cooked in slow oven.

title: mexiburgers
directions: Brown ground beef,
onion,
salt
and pepper and drain. Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve on buns.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape into balls, melt shortening in large skillet, brown and cook meatballs.
Set meatballs aside.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into skillet.
Stir until thickened.
Add meatballs, pineapple tidbits and green peppers.
Serve over rice.

title: molded candies(diabetic recipe)
directions: Beat shortening and water until fluffy.
Stir in sugar replacement; knead until smooth.
Continue as follows for individual molds.

title: pecan chip pie
directions: Place pecans and chips in bottom of pie crust. Mix eggs, karo, sugar, water and vanilla together. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In several Dutch ovens, over medium heat, brown beef and onions; drain.
Add the taco seasoning, tomato sauce and tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs (hard-boiled).
Cool, peel, slice in half and remove centers.
Blend centers, mustard and mayo of equal parts until creamy.
Chop olives and add to egg mixture.
Fill egg white halves with mixture.
Garnish with olive slice and sprinkle of paprika.
Chill until served.
Makes 24 eggs.

title: horseradish
directions: Dig horseradish in early spring or late fall.
Cut off tops and replant.
Scrub roots. Cut out bad spots.
Cut in chunks. Grind with as little water as possible.
Reuse horseradish water if grinding a small amount at a time to reserve the flavor.
Grind finely.
Add ingredients.
All quantities are approximate.
Add more or less to taste.

title: chocolate chip snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, walnuts, baking soda and salt with fork in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Mix in water, oil and vinegar.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all together and roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Then roll in sugar.
Place on
an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place a chocolate star/Kiss in center of each as soon as baked.

title: italian cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, oil and egg yolks together.
Add flour and soda and sift together.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and then add coconut. Bake at 350°.

title: holiday cranberry apricot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a double boiler; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until all sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat; simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Continue cooking until thick.
If mixture still seems too thin, add 1/4 teaspoon of cornstarch, mixed in a little cold water to thicken. Serve with pork or poultry.
Delicious and different!
Makes a great gift when packaged in a decorative glass jar!

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate. Sprinkle
with crushed pecans or walnuts before refrigeration. (Good summertime dessert.)

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into ball.
Chill until firm.
I usually roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: italiano bread
directions: Defrost bread dough.
Hand chop the sausage, ham and cheese. Mix the chopped ingredients together in a bowl.
Dice celery, bell peppers and jalapeno peppers.
Add these seasonings with pimento, for coloring, to the bowl of chopped ingredients.
Season to taste.

title: lemon jello cake(a tart, lemony pound cake)
directions: Combine Jello and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Pour the boiling water over them and stir until dissolved.
Add the oil and lemon extract and stir.
Add in the cake mix and beat thoroughly. Add the eggs, one at a time and mix for 1 minute after each.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for about an hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for about 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on rack.
Make a glaze of powdered sugar and real lemon juice and drizzle over the warm cake.
You can make as much glaze as you like and make it as thick or think as you like by adjusting either of the ingredients.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Stir in balance; drop onto waxed paper.
Let harden.
Makes about 80 pieces.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in order listed; mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread oats into large shallow pan. Bake 10 minutes to toast (turn as needed).
Toss with sugar, nuts and melted butter.
Press evenly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza
directions: Cut French bread in half, then spread with pizza sauce.
Add cheese and toppings as desired.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
Bring 2 sticks oleo, 5 tablespoons cocoa and water to a boil.
Add buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Pour over the sugar and flour and mix well.
Mix all well and pour in greased cake pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: individual barbecue taco salads
directions: Brown meat; drain and add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Heat thoroughly.
Add process cheese spread.
Stir until melted.
Then arrange lettuce in cups. Fill each cup with meat mixture, chopped tomatoes and corn chips.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Add all ingredients to melted margarine.
Remove pie shells from original foil pans and place in Pyrex pie plates or heavy pie pan.
Pour mixture into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and freeze. Keep cold after cutting.

title: snowball dip
directions: With sharp knife, cut top from bread.
Set aside.
Hollow loaf, leaving a 1 1/2 to 2-inch thick shell.
Cut removed bread into cubes (set aside).
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in clams, reserved clam liquid, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, pepper sauce and salt until well blended.
On baking sheet, make a cross with 2 sheets aluminum foil, each long enough to cover loaf.
Pour clam mixture into shell.
Cover with top of bread.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours and wrap in foil.
Serve with cut up vegetables for dipping and bread cubes.

title: 10 day date and nut cake
directions: Mix dates with boiling water. Cool to lukewarm. Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in date mixture and add soda, flour and salt. Add the nuts. Bake in ungreased tube pan at 350° until done, about 60 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill several hours in refrigerator.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in a large pot until tender.
In another pan, saute onions, garlic, celery and bell pepper in the butter and cooking oil.
Toast the 4 slices of bread and soak in the condensed milk.
When the cabbage is boiled, drain.
Add the ingredients to the cabbage, including the oil and butter; mix. Chop up the bread and add to the
mixture.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
Put in a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 400° until brown.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix ingredients in a microwave safe dish. Put in microwave and cook on High for 4 minutes. Take out and stir; replace in microwave and cook on High for 4 minutes more. Take out; add 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir and mix well. Put in microwave for 2 minutes on High. Take out; add 1 teaspoon baking soda. Stir until light and fluffy. Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Spread thin as possible.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and set aside.
Mix sugar, salt, water and shortening to your yeast.
Then add flour until dough is stiff.
Let rise for 15 to 20 minutes, then beat down.
Let rise for 15 to 20 minutes, then cook for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
After mixing slowly, mix in Rice Krispies.
Put in refrigerator until mixture is cold.
Roll cooled mixture into round balls.
Recool balls after formed.
Dip balls into chocolate and paraffin mix with a toothpick and put on wax paper to dry.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: hummingbird cake with frosting
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add eggs and oil; stirring until moistened.
Add bananas, pineapple (with juice), pecans and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and salt to just done.
Drain.
Add mayonnaise, cheese and green onion.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes (or mix all together, refrigerate and heat).

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix strawberries, jello and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and turn off heat.
Let it cool.
Mix large instant pudding according to directions.
Add large sour cream and large Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Cover bottom of large glass bowl with vanilla wafers.
Cover with pudding mix.
Then add a layer of the strawberry mixture.
Continue to layer until you use all.
This is a very big pudding.

title: salsa dip
directions: Microwave salsa and cheese in a microwave bowl on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring after 2 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frosted chocolate cookies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Cool; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add next ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Chill. Roll into balls (any size) and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet (greased) and bake for 10 minutes in 325° oven.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Cover with soup and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix everything together except the chilies and cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Spread with chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350°.

title: peppermint taffy
directions: Grease 2 baking pans (8 x 8 x 2-inches) with butter or margarine.
Heat all ingredients, except extract and coloring, to just boiling in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook, without stirring, to 256° on candy thermometer (about 30 minutes).
Remove from heat and add peppermint extract.
Pour half the mixture into a pan.
Add food coloring to the other half of mixture and pour in the other pan.
Let cool about 15 minutes, until cool in center.
Fold, double and pull each color of taffy until stiff and light in color.
Pull each color into long strips and twist together.
Cut into 1 to 3-inch sections with scissors and wrap with wax paper.
(Taffy will lose its shape if not wrapped.)

title: oven potato puff
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
In 3-quart covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 minutes until tender. Drain and mash.
Cover and set aside.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
In large mixing bowl at high speed, beat cottage cheese and eggs for 2 minutes.
At low speed, beat in sour cream, onions, butter, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and beat until well blended.
Transfer to baking dish.
If making ahead, cover and refrigerate until 30 minutes before baking.
About 1 hour before serving, drizzle top of potatoes with butter.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 minutes or until heated in center and lightly brown.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Boil 1 cup water.
Pour over lemon jello and set aside.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Set aside.
Beat evaporated milk which has been chilled.
Add jello mixture to cream cheese mixture. Blend.
Combine this mixture with beaten milk.
Gently stir to mix. Add vanilla and pour mixture into crust.
Chill several hours.

title: low country one-pot dinner
directions: Slice sausage into 2 to 3-inch pieces and place in large pot with the corn.
Add water and seasoning and boil 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and additional seasoning and boil until everything is tender.

title: dirt cups
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Sprinkle crushed cookies in bottom of 6 clear plastic cups, add chocolate pudding and gummy worms.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Makes 6 cups of dirt.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add macaroni and salt.
