Stir to separate.
Return to boil.
Boil, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 9 to 12 minutes or until desired tenderness.
Drain. Cut cheese into small chunks and add to macaroni.
Add milk and butter.
Return to heat and cook until cheese melts.
Pour into serving dish and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with the onion, sausage and bell pepper.
Drain.
Put in large pot and add other ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add dry ingredients to taste.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle pepper, garlic and onion powder to taste.
Put mushroom soup over chicken; then layer cheese slices on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and put in a 400° oven for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ham dip
directions: Blend together well and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cucumbers with dressing
directions: In bowl combine mayo, sugar, vinegar, and salt. Add cucumbers. Stir to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hrs.

title: batter for franks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in cornmeal. Cut in shortening.
Add and stir until blended, the egg and milk. Dip into batter 8 to 12 wieners.
Fry in deep, hot fat (365°) until brown, about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Insert wooden skewer in end of each frankfurter. Serve with catsup.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then 3 cups of flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix remaining flour with cherries, pineapple and broken pecans.
Stir into batter. Add vanilla. Pour into greased tube cake pan that has been lined with brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Let cool in pan before you take it up.

title: daddy's favorite cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough and let rise.
Once doubled in size, roll out on counter to half-inch thickness.
Use back of spoon to spread soft butter over dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Sprinkle with Equal for desired sweetness.
Roll dough up like a jelly roll. Then slice about 1-inch thick.
Place in pan and let rise again until doubled when desired height.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Frost if desired.

title: escabeche(guatemala)
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and fry until brown.
Remove from pan or boil the whole chicken in 8-10 cups of water with a 1/2 tsp. salt.
Remove and bake in oven until golden brown.
Remove meat from bones and save the stock.
Cut onions into thin slices and soak in vinegar and 1/2 cup of water.
Pour water into large sauce pan.
Add the seasonings and whole peppers, boil for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and boil for 10 more minutes.
Add the onions and vinegar to taste.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with corn tortillas.

title: carbonades a la flammande
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in hot oil.

title: frozen salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into dish that can go in freezer.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add oil and eggs. Roll into small balls. Put 1-inch apart on cookie sheet. Bake in 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ground beef and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with noodles or onions after casserole has cooked about 30 to 35 minutes.
Brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cool corn bread; crumble.
Mix tomatoes, relish, onion and pepper.
Drain liquid from vegetables.
Reserve liquid and mix with mayonnaise.
Mix vegetables and corn bread together.
Pour 1/2 mixture into pan; put half of mayonnaise on top; add remaining corn bread mixture; add remaining mayonnaise on top.

title: carrots l'orange(pour les rabbits avec les yeux ruined)
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until tender-crisp.
In a separate pot, combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Add orange juice and cook stirring constantly until thickened, boiling for 1 minute.
Stir in butter and remove from heat.
Pour over hot, drained carrots, tossing gently to coat evenly.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: Mix sugar and juice.
Bring to boil.
Add beaten eggs and jello; let cool.
Whip milk and fold into mixture.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with strawberries and chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Stir in walnuts and coconut.
In another bowl, combine oil and eggs and beat 1 minute.
Stir in carrots and pineapple. Combine the two mixtures, wet and dry.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Put in blender in order listed.
Enjoy!

title: ready pie crust
directions: Mix with pie crust blender in large bowl.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
May be kept for several weeks.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Heat shortening, onion and mangoes together for 3 minutes.
Add beef, pepper and salt and blend thoroughly, then remove from heat. Add eggs and blend.
Stir in corn and tomatoes.
Pour in casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut together for the icing. Place in refrigerator overnight in airtight container.
Bake cake mix in two layers; cut layers in half, making 4 thin layers.
When layers are cold, ice with icing and store in airtight container in refrigerator for four days before cutting.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Grease two 8-inch layer pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper. Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Stir in next 3 ingredients together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend until smooth. Add vanilla. Stir in flour mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on racks. Split cake layers in half. Spread between layers with filling.

title: pancakes
directions: Add biscuit mix, milk, sugar and eggs together.
For thinner pancakes add more milk. Heat frying pan and using Crisco shortening, fry until golden on each side.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender at slow speed and pour into two (8 or 9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake 10 minutes on 400° and 20 minutes on 350°.
Maybe a little longer until set.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in mixer- pour into greased 9 x 9 pyrex dish and bake 60 minutes at 325 degrees.
Even more moist second day- if it lasts that long.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine and dates.
Add all ingredients, except Rice Krispies and coconut.
Cook for 6 minutes until all ingredients dissolve, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Cool and store in plastic container.
Will last up to 2 weeks.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, parsley, onions and seasonings.
Add rice and shrimp; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Slightly crush corn flakes; combine with melted butter and almonds; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: open-faced peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Line pie shell with peaches.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Bake in shell for 10 minutes.
Take out and turn oven to 350°.
Mix the egg, sugar, flour and butter.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Put orange juice and rind in measuring cup and add shortening and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Stir into dry ingredients and add cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans; let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: great macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, vegetables and beans according to package directions.

title: sister erma lee's cucumber lime pickles
directions: Mix 2 cups lime to 2 gallons water.
Soak cucumbers for 24 hours; stir occasionally in lime water.
Soak in crockery or enamel ware (do not use aluminum ware).
Remove from lime water and rinse three times in cool water.
Soak three hours in ice water.
Remove carefully to drain.

title: crispy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
May add 1/4 cup shredded carrots.
Makes 10 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, then add sugars and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed. Drop by tablespoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: diet soup
directions: Mix all together. Cook about 1 hour or until well done.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place fruit in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle water and sugar over fruit.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon.
Beat egg thoroughly. Pour slowly over Bisquick mixture in a thin stream, stirring with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over fruit.
Pour butter over all.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until golden. Serve hot or cold with milk or cream.

title: curried chicken salad from new jersey
directions: Combine chicken, orange slices, nuts, apples, raisins and grapes.
Stir together mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss to mix.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana freeze
directions: Whiz ingredients in a blender and serve.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thick. Place slice of ham and cheese and sprinkle with mushrooms on each tortilla and roll up.
Place folded side down in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour white sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Combine flour and Crisco until crumbly.
Add buttermilk.
Mix until smooth and flour as needed.
Knead into a ball and roll out on floured surface.
Cut in small biscuits and bake at 400° until brown.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown trimmed meat in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
When meat is tender enough (approximately 2 to 3 hours), use 2 forks to shred or pull apart the meat.
Continue cooking until the meat is very tender (cooking time can vary from 3 to 6 hours).
Serve alone or on buns. Serves 12.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in plastic bag or covered bowl.
Cut biscuits in fourths.
Coat each piece with sugar/cinnamon mixture.
(Do about 10 to 12 pieces together.)
Put pieces into a greased pan. Melt margarine.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done; peel.
Put in mixer.
Add sugar; mix together good.
Add butter, then add milk, as if you were making mashed potatoes.
Add spices.
You want the mixture runny, then pour into pie shells.
Bake for about an hour, or until done, at 350°.

title: golden potato soup
directions: In a large pan combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, bouillon and seasonings. Mix well. Cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended. Add the milk/flour mixture to the vegetables and cook until thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: stir-fried spinach
directions: Rinse spinach well and remove tough stems.
Coarsely chop. Melt butter in a saute pan and saute garlic lightly without browning.
Add spinach; toss and cover, cooking just a few minutes, until spinach is wilted.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and toss again before serving.
Serves 4.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in 1 1/2 to 2-inch thick rounds.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with olive oil.
Sprinkle well with lemon pepper.
Bake in 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes very thin and boil for 5 minutes.
Heat all other ingredients until cheese melts.
Place potatoes in casserole and pour the other ingredients over the top.
Bake on 400° until sauce is bubbly.

title: delicious high fiber gems(no salt, no fat, no eggs, no sugar)
directions: Mix flour and bran or germ in a large bowl.
Add milk with the vinegar in it and mix in with molasses until well mixed.
Measure the 3/4 cup of hard boiling water and stir in 1/2 tablespoon baking soda.
Mix all well.
Bake in greased muffin tins or iron gem tins, making 15, large or proportionately small ones.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool slightly and remove from pans.
These are best if stored for a day and are to be eaten cold.
Good in lunches.
Good with a bit of butter.
Recipe is 85 years old, used for five generations.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Place in buttered dish and chill.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all together and add 3 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry and line pie pan.
Stir together sugar, orange peel and cornstarch.
Stir in rhubarb. Place in pastry lined pie pan and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits in it.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Put in crock-pot on low for 2 hours.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut, nuts and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir together until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into pan; allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liners 3/4 full with cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top with fruit or berries.

title: tangy lemon bars
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar together.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press into greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix and freeze in 9x13 inch pan. Cut in squares and serve.

title: apricot pies
directions: Cover apricots with water in saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes until soft.
Drain excess water.
Mix and mash with fork until preserve like.
Add sugar.
Mix.
Quarter each pie crust.
Drop apricot mixture into middle of crust.
Fold to cover apricots.
Go around edges with fork to keep apricots inside.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: angel delight salad
directions: First dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water and juice from the pineapple.
Add marshmallows and stir well, then chill. Fix in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Add coconut, pecans and pineapple. Fold in whipped whipping cream and chill for 1 or 2 hours to set.

title: salmon mousse(great party dip with crackers)
directions: Put ingredients into food processor until well blended.
Put in serving dip bowl.
Serve with crackers.
Add a bit of whitefish for milder flavor.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all together.
Makes large cake.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients (except noodles) to large pot and cook until boiling. Add salt, pepper, and garlic salt to taste. About 5-10 minutes before serving add uncooked macaroni noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add eggs, cheese, mayonnaise, soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with buttered snack cracker crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken.
Boil spaghetti in broth.
Add onion and pepper. Add soups, pimentos and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix meat, rice, cream of mushroom soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into small, round balls; place in shallow pan. Cover with tomato soup, mixed with water.
Makes approximately 15 meat balls.
Bake in a slow oven for 2 hours, covered.

title: fresh vegetable basil soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, celery and carrot.
Cook until soft (about 10 minutes).
Add potato, tomatoes, vegetable stock and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cauliflower and zucchini.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Add peas. Simmer another 5 minutes or until all vegetables are tender. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: holiday meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat out meat, one-inch thick, onto cutting board.
Cut into one-inch cubes.
Roll cubes into balls.
Place onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Meatballs may be frozen or served at this point.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix together brown sugar, flour and oatmeal with enough melted butter to hold it together when pressed in your hand.
Press 3/4 of mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. While baking, thicken cherries with cornstarch and flavor with almond extract.
Layer cherries onto crust and sprinkle with remaining crisp.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in 1 bowl; set aside.
Mix all wet ingredients in another bowl.
Use 3 or 4 loaf pans; grease and flour lightly.
Mix dry ingredients with wet; blend in well.
Pour in loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes (stick a toothpick in bread and if clean, they are done).

title: pizza salad
directions: Pour over salad before serving.

title: cool whip summer dessert
directions: Mix all together and keep cold.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil water and oleo.
Take off heat and add flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread batter on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Prepare 2 small boxes French vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Beat in cream cheese (softened).
Pour over cooled crust.
Spread Cool Whip over top and then chocolate syrup.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries
until they pop.
Make jello and allow to thicken.
Mix
all	ingredients in cold cranberries, except the whipping cream.
Let stand overnight.
Whip cream and add.

title: magic muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
20 muffins.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat 3 eggs real good.
Add 1 cup sugar, cocoa, cornstarch or flour after you have mixed all them together good.
Place all together in a boiler and add sweet milk.
Cook very slow, stirring all the time.
Let cook until it's very stiff.
Take off stove. Pour in baked pie crust.

title: baked pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops and season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix the milk and soup.
Place 1/3 of the soup in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chops in the pan.
Add potatoes and onion, cover with remainder of the soup.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: seafood marinade
directions: Marinate seafood 2 hours.
Bake, broil or grill.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, trim and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems, finely chop. Melt 3 tablespoons margarine.
Cook and stir stems, pepper and onion until tender.
Remove from heat and add bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in shallow baking dish. Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Place mushrooms filled side up in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: perfect meatballs
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, onion and salt; mix well.
Add beef and mix thoroughly.
Divide mixture into 8 equal parts.
Roll each part (like a sausage) into a 6-inch length.
Lay the 8 pieces side by side and use a knife to cut into 1-inch pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball.
Place the meatballs into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add to spaghetti sauce or use in a cocktail recipe.

title: puddin' sandwiches
directions: Combine yogurt and peanut butter until smooth. Place large spoonful between 2 crackers and freeze.
Great after school or summertime snack.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: potatoes and cheese
directions: Put enough thinly sliced potatoes to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with onions, then bacon (crumbled) and American cheese.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Continue layering until pan is full.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: vivian stauffer's rhubarb cream pie
directions: In a large skillet, combine butter, rhubarb and sugar.
Cook slowly until rhubarb is tender. Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and add to rhubarb mixture. Cook until thick.
Cool and pour into baked 8-inch pie shell. Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: chicken curry
directions: Prepare rice by package directions.
Cool.
Cook and cube chicken breasts.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Drop by small teaspoon and bake at 325° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: caramel or chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine and cook over medium heat until it comes to a boil, then boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove and add butterscotch morsels and Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
When mixed pour on a greased pan.
Cool overnight and cut into squares.

title: mary ann's world famous cheesecake
directions: Mix together and put in a 9-inch spring-form pan; press down with wax paper.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain fruits well; mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: haystacks
directions: Bring oleo, milk, sugar and cocoa to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Add coconut, oatmeal and vanilla, making sure the oatmeal is covered.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Let them cool; they will set up when cool.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute
onion
and
pepper
in margarine.
Dissolve beef bouillon in
hot water.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 quart casserole.
Bake
for 30 to 35 minutes until water is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: nine-layer dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream with envelope of taco mix.
Then spread each ingredient in order given in thin layers in a shallow dish.
Serve with tortillas or corn chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Use a wooden spoon.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Mix sugar, water and Karo.
Cook until syrup strings a hair.
Add pecans and cook and stir occasionally until golden brown.
Take off heat and add salt and butter.
Stir until butter melted.
Add soda and vanilla.
Beat vigorously until it foams up.
Pour onto cookie sheets.
Spread as thin as possible.
Let cool until hard.
Peel off foil.

title: raspberry jam squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and shortening until blended with a fork.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Spread 1/2 mixture into greased square pan and press down.
Spread with raspberry jam. Sprinkle rest of flour mixture on top of jam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut and enjoy!

title: osgood pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten yolks, nuts and raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour into pie mixture. Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This can be made ahead and frozen.

title: christmas popcorn teddy bear
directions: You will need a ribbon (optional).
Place popcorn in large, greased bowl.
Combine corn syrup and sugar in medium saucepan. Bring to full, rolling boil, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Pour over popcorn; toss to coat well.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns; combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/2 cup margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with mixed corn flakes and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: green apple pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour and spices.
Layer apples in pie crust, then sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Continue to layer until shell is full.
Top with second crust.
Mix a little melted butter with brown sugar and put over top crust.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: witches kisses
directions: In a large bowl, beat, on medium speed, egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks appear.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold in chocolate morsels, walnuts and coconut.

title: aunt gertie mae's punch
directions: Make orange juice, jello, lemonade and cherry Kool-Aid as package directions.
Mix all together along with the pineapple juice.
Freeze ice cream and cut into squares.
Freeze 2 trays of punch with cherries and add to mixture.

title: hamburger stuff
directions: Prepare stuffing per instructions on package.
Cook hamburger, onion and mushrooms together in large skillet until meat is brown and crumbly.
Drain excess fat from meat mixture.
Add to stuffing and serve.
Very flexible; can feed 10 to 25 people.

title: microwave barbecue shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp; drain well.
Sprinkle shrimp with pepper combination in microwave dish.
Pour over shrimp the butter, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Cook on High 10 to 12 minutes; stir twice.
When shrimp are pink and tender, remove.
Add 2 teaspoons salt after cooking.
Let stand 3 minutes. Serve with French bread for dipping in sauce.
Tossed salad and best friends make this a "super" bowl.

title: german slaw
directions: Put the cabbage in bowl. Add onions. Then add the peppers (do not stir). Sprinkle the sugar on top (without stirring). Boil the oil, vinegar, dry mustard, salt and celery salt. Pour this over the cabbage mixture (without stirring). Put in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours before stirring. Let set several hours before serving.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: "gumbo"
directions: Brown meat, adding cut up onion.
While this is cooking, combine tomatoes, rice, sugar and okra (if frozen) in a bowl. This moistens rice and starts thawing of okra.
When meat browns, drain any excess fat.
Add vegetable-rice mixture, stir together, cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add seasonings with veggies or halfway through simmering (celery seed or other spices could be added).
Serve with bread.
Better even the next day!

title: easy fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients (except nuts) to 234°.
Add nuts and beat until firm.
Let it cool in pan. Spread on wax paper on a cookie sheet. (Can be made into cookies.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; set aside 2 cups of broth.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup with 1 cup of broth and pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and put with 1 cup broth.
Mix with cornbread mix.
Spoon over soup mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: tomato juice freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an ice cube tray and freeze until quite firm.
This will take less than an hour in most refrigerators.
Spoon mixture into sherbet glasses.
Top each serving with a sprig of parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serve with a couple of crackers or at Christmastime, serve with Scramble (toasted cereals).

title: ham strata
directions: Remove crusts from bread and put crusts into 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese over crust scraps. Cut bread slices into angles and arrange over layers.
Combine slightly beaten eggs, milk, onion, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water in a covered saucepan for 25 minutes, or until tender.
Drain well.
Dissolve cornstarch in pineapple juice.
Add with cinnamon and sugar to carrots; simmer until thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings. Freezes well.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat in a crock-pot (or pot on stove) the pork and beans, tomato soup, tomato paste, and cheese (cut into small chunks).
In a frypan, brown ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper together.
Drain; add to mixture in crock-pot.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: deer jerky
directions: Slice steak across grain 1/3 inch thick.
Blend sauces and seasonings in bowl.
Add steak slices.
Marinate 24 hours. Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 150° with oven door ajar for 8 to 10 hours or until completely dry, turning every 2 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: klugo cream cake
directions: Make
cake
according
to
package
directions. Bake in greased and
floured
jelly
roll
pan for 20 minutes at 350°. Best to
leave in pan.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Spread on cake. Refrigerate for 1 hour, then top with crushed
pineapple and slice bananas on top. Top all this with whipped cream. Garnish
with
your	choice	of
fruit and nuts. Chopped pecans and cherries are nice.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cheeses and mix together with onion, salt and pepper. Add chopped crab.
Spread in glass pie plate; top with almonds. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Cool (do not drain).
Gradually add sugar to shortening, beating well.
Stir in raisins, liquid and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add raisin mixture, stirring after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked sauerkraut
directions: Fry sausage until brown. Drain off fat and mix with other ingredients (reserving a few bread crumbs). Put all into baking dish and sprinkle reserved crumbs on top. Pour 3/4 cup milk over top and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine the above.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: mushroom stew
directions: Fry in oil onions, green peppers and celery.
In large pan, add tomatoes, tomato soup and tomato paste.
Break up the sausage and pork chops, then add to the ingredients.
Simmer for 3 hours, stirring often.
Just before serving, add the mushrooms.
Serve the mushroom stew over sliced Italian bread.

title: citrus sage chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry; place in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over chicken and bake 20 minutes.
Turn each piece and cover with remaining sauce.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Serves 8.

title: sugarless sweet potatoes 'n fruit
directions: Spray a baking dish with Pam to prevent sticking.
Drain sweet potatoes and place in the dish.
Peel orange and separate into segments.
Place on top of the potatoes.
Sprinkle with sugar substitute and cinnamon.
Add raisins.
Pour orange or pineapple juice over top.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
8 servings.
Exchanges:
1 serving = 1/2 fruit, 1 bread.
Calories: 1 serving, 95.

title: mocha cinnamon fingers
directions: In small bowl, mix coffee crystals, water and vanilla until coffee is dissolved.
In medium bowl, stir together flour and cinnamon.

title: good corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion and cook until clear and soft.
Drain off fat.
Add corn, seasoning and chicken broth. Lastly, add hot milk.
Enjoy.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain drippings.
Add chili seasoning to hamburger on low heat.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add hamburger mixture.
Cook on medium heat until done.
Serve.

title: elephant stew(this is a fun recipe from my uncle in utah.)
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over heat for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3800 people.
If more are expected, add the rabbits, but do this only if necessary; some people do not like hair in their stew.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Place all ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Cook slowly over LOW heat on burner, stirring frequently, until cheese melts and all is hot. Do not add any liquid. It makes its own. Serve hot.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add vinegar, water, tomato catsup, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix mustard, chili powder, cayenne pepper, salt, sugar and bay leaves; add to other mixture. Add cloves of garlic and onion.
Cook together for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 cups, enough to swab 4 to 5 pounds of meat.

title: swedish cakes
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and flour. Form into small balls.
Roll into egg white and chopped nuts. Place on greased cookie sheet; press fairly flat with bottom of small glass.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish (spray with Pam).
Put cheese on top and bake in
a 350° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven. Saute onions in butter. Drain clams reserving juice. Add water to clam juice to equal 1 cup. To the onion mixture add potatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, pepper and clam juice. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Mash potatoes slightly with the back of a spoon against the side of the Dutch oven. Stir together milk and half and half cream. Add flour to milk mixture and stir well. Slowly add milk mixture to potato mixture. Cook and stir until thickened. Add clams and heat for 2 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: cornish hens and rice
directions: Place raw rice in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with chicken broth.
Cut hens in half (or the chicken pieces).
Shake in the dry onion soup mix and lay on rice mixture.
Pour 1 can mushroom soup mixed with 1 cup hot water over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour uncovered, 1 hour covered, 10 more minutes uncovered.

title: mounds candy
directions: Melt butter in milk over low heat, stirring.
Remove from heat and stir sugar and coconut into milk mixture.
This mixture is very soft and more confectioners sugar may be added to make a firmer mixture.
Spoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cut coconut mixture into 1-inch pieces.
Refrigerate 2 hours or freeze 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over low heat.
Dip coconut pieces in; place on foil in refrigerator.
Use spatula when placing into a container with lid.
Crumble plastic between layers.
Refrigerate.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an 8-inch square pan in which the tablespoon of butter has been melted.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: best ever venison
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into meat.
Brown onion in shortening and remove.
Brown meat.
Place meat in a large casserole.
Put onion on top of meat.
Mix sauces and pour on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion, carrot, apple and celery and cook, uncovered, on moderate heat for 5 minutes until onion is soft.
Blend in flour and curry powder and cook, stirring, 1 minute longer.
Add chicken broth, tomatoes, mace, nutmeg and black pepper.
Raise heat to moderately high; cover and bring to boil.
Adjust heat to mixture bubbles gently. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove and discard cloves.
Cool soup for 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; cook macaroni.
Combine hamburger, macaroni and sauce.
Put in 13 x 9 baking dish.
Top with cheese and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.
